20ceremony%20on%20July%208%2C%20attended%20by%20Bollywood's%20glitterati%2C%20creating%20a%20buzz%20with%20unseen%20photos%20of%20the%20couple%20circulating%20on%20social%20media.%20In%20the%20viral%20pictures%2C%20Anant%20and%20Radhika%20are%20captured%20sharing%20joyful%20moments%20together%2C%20visibly%20immersed%20in%20each%20other's%20company.%20Anant%20donned%20a%20mustard%20yellow%20kurta%20paired%20with%20intricately%20designed%20white%20pajamas%2C%20complemented%20by%20his%20neatly%20tied%20back%20hair%2C%20exuding%20a%20handsome%20charm.%20Radhika%20looked%20resplendent%20in%20a%20yellow%20lehenga%20adorned%20with%20a%20floral%20chunni%2C%20accompanied%20by%20a%20floral%20necklace%20and%20maang%20tikka%2C%20which%20accentuated%20her%20elegant%20Haldi%20ensemble.%20The%20star-studded%20Haldi%20ceremony%20saw%20the%20presence%20of%20Bollywood%20celebrities%20like%20Salman%20Khan%2C%20Ranveer%20Singh%2C%20Ananya%20Panday%2C%20Arjun%20Kapoor%2C%20Janhvi%20Kapoor%2C%20Khushi%20Kapoor%2C%20Vedang%20Raina%2C%20Orry%2C%20Sara%20Ali%20Khan%2C%20and%20Manushi%20Chhillar.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fanant-ambani-and-radhika-merchants-unseen-haldi-ceremony-pictures-the-couple-glows-with-joy%2Farticleshow%2F111632989.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Locked%20out%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20collage%20of%20two%20blue%20silhouettes%20and%20various%20housing-related%20imagery.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667bf61040cf2af6e4f5d1bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAndrei%20Cojocaru%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlfred%20Perry%20got%20word%20on%20Labor%20Day%20weekend.%20He'd%20just%20thrown%20one%20of%20his%20signature%20cookouts%20in%20the%20courtyard%20of%20his%20apartment%20complex%20in%20Las%20Vegas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20kind%20of%20laid-back%20life%20he%20came%20southwest%20for.%20A%20Chrysler%20retiree%20from%20the%20Detroit%20suburbs%2C%20Perry%20enjoyed%20the%20warm%20weather%20and%20lights%20of%20Vegas%20as%20he%20was%20driving%20through%20over%20three%20years%20ago.%20He%20decided%20to%20stay.%20As%20luck%20would%20have%20it%2C%20he%20said%2C%20he%20had%20enough%20left%20from%20his%20pension%20and%20Social%20Security%20checks%20when%20Dan%20Wright%20offered%20him%20a%20studio%20apartment%20downtown.%20Perry%20put%20down%20the%20first%20month's%20rent%20and%20a%20deposit%20and%20moved%20in%20shortly%20after.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20a%20relative%20told%20him%20to%20come%20back%20to%20the%20Midwest%20to%20handle%20a%20family%20emergency%20that%20September%20of%202022%2C%20Perry%20didn't%20hesitate.%20He%20had%20paid%20that%20month's%20rent%2C%20he%20said%2C%20and%20set%20out%20on%20the%20long%20trek%20to%20fetch%20his%205-year-old%20son%2C%20whose%20mother%20was%20in%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Perry%20arrived%20back%20home%20with%20the%20boy%20about%20a%20month%20later%2C%20his%20keys%20no%20longer%20opened%20the%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWright%20had%20been%20having%20issues%20with%20Perry%20over%20visitors%20to%20his%20apartment.%20So%20Perry%20was%20anxious%20that%20Wright%20wanted%20him%20out.%20The%20night%20Perry%20came%20back%20in%20the%20wee%20hours%2C%20he%20said%2C%20he%20and%20his%20son%20stayed%20with%20a%20neighbor.%20The%20next%20day%2C%20he%20said%2C%20Wright%20refused%20to%20let%20him%20back%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Man%20standing%20with%20hands%20in%20his%20pockets%20against%20a%20blue%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667cba4750b021b5cae9cd70%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlfred%20Perry%20filed%20a%20complaint%20saying%20he%20was%20locked%20out%20of%20his%20Las%20Vegas%20apartment%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202022.%20He%20and%20his%20son%20ended%20up%20sleeping%20in%20his%20Jeep.%3Cp%3EBridget%20Bennett%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPerry%20and%20his%20son%20started%20living%20out%20of%20his%20Jeep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrevious%20convictions%20for%20drug%20possession%20made%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehousingcenter.org%2Fhousing-resources%2Fcriminal-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinding%20a%20new%20apartment%3C%2Fa%3E%20difficult.%20Months%20passed%20with%20the%20pair%20living%20out%20of%20Perry's%20car.%20Someone%20reported%20the%20situation%20to%20law%20enforcement%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20North%20Las%20Vegas%20Police%20Department%20said%2C%20and%20officers%20pulled%20Perry%20over%20to%20do%20a%20welfare%20check%20on%20his%20son.%20Officers%20arrested%20Perry%20on%20charges%20including%20child%20neglect%20and%20driving%20without%20a%20license%20and%20turned%20his%20son%20over%20to%20Child%20Protective%20Services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerry%20said%20he%20spent%20a%20year%20trying%20to%20regain%20custody.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20take%20my%20share%20of%20the%20blame%20for%20having%20my%20son%20out%20there%20like%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Perry%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20Dan%20hadn't%20locked%20me%20out%2C%20I'd%20still%20have%20my%20son%20today.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerry%20filed%20a%20complaint%20saying%20Wright%20had%20locked%20him%20out%20illegally.%20That's%20when%20a%20landlord%20turns%20off%20utilities%2C%20changes%20locks%2C%20or%20otherwise%20keeps%20tenants%20from%20their%20home%20without%20first%20getting%20a%20judge's%20consent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProtections%20against%20these%20kinds%20of%20extrajudicial%20evictions%20date%20back%20centuries.%20Today%2C%20lockouts%20are%20criminalized%20in%20six%20US%20states%2C%20punishable%20by%20imprisonment%2C%20and%20are%20banned%20by%20civil%20statutes%2C%20enforceable%20by%20fines%20and%20civil%20suits%2C%20in%20those%20states%20and%2039%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20Business%20Insider%20investigation%20has%20found%20that%20in%20cities%20across%20the%20United%20States%2C%20complaints%20about%20lockouts%20are%20on%20the%20rise.%20Tenants%20in%20crisis%20are%20mostly%20stuck%20calling%20the%20police%2C%20who%20rarely%20take%20action%20against%20property%20owners%20who%20may%20have%20broken%20the%20law%2C%20BI%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20police%20departments%20even%20instruct%20responding%20officers%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20get%20involved%2C%20leaving%20tenants%20to%20face%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhomelesslaw.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F10%2FProtectTenants2018.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esudden%20homelessness%3C%2Fa%3E%20despite%20civil%20and%20criminal%20laws%20intended%20to%20protect%20them%20from%20precisely%20that%20fate.%20The%20absence%20of%20a%20federal%20law%20banning%20lockouts%2C%20a%20patchwork%20of%20state%20laws%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20police%20action%2C%20and%20an%20uphill%20battle%20for%20tenants%20in%20court%20have%20together%20allowed%20many%20landlords%20to%20lock%20tenants%20out%20with%20impunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FYPRO3%2F3%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Complaints%20about%20illegal%20lockouts%20are%20on%20the%20rise%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22544%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nature%20of%20illegal%20lockouts%20means%20they%20are%20hard%20to%20track%20directly.%20To%20gauge%20how%20often%20they%20happen%2C%20BI%20reviewed%20thousands%20of%20911%20calls%2C%20housing%20complaints%2C%20and%20court%20records%20and%20found%20evidence%20suggesting%20that%20illegal%20lockouts%20have%20increased%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20rise%20comes%20as%20half%20of%20all%20US%20renters%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jchs.harvard.edu%2Fpress-releases%2Fnew-report-shows-rent-unaffordable-half-renters-cost-burdens-surge-record-levels%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2022%20million%20households%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20are%20facing%20financial%20stress%20over%20housing%20costs%2C%20spending%20more%20than%2030%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20rent%20and%20utilities%2C%20a%20burden%20that%20makes%20it%20easy%20to%20fall%20behind%20on%20rent%2C%20and%20catastrophic%20to%20be%20abruptly%20thrown%20out%20into%20a%20tight%20rental%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rise%20in%20lockout%20complaints%20also%20came%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspeculative-home-flippers-signal-housing-markets-peak-real-estate-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20investors%20sought%20to%20cash%20in%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20residential%20property%20management%20and%20ownership%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20Some%20of%20them%20were%20inexperienced%20first-time%20landlords%20who%20may%20have%20been%20unfamiliar%20with%20landlord-tenant%20laws.%20Others%20were%20corporations%20and%20private-equity%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20more%20from%20our%20series%20on%20illegal%20evictions%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flandlord-illegal-lockout-court-tenant-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhen%20renters%20get%20locked%20out%2C%20they%20may%20never%20get%20back%20in%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finformal-rental-agreement-affordable-housing-illegal-lockout-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnprotected%20at%20the%20margins%20of%20the%20rental%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELandlords%20have%20a%20variety%20of%20motivations%20for%20wanting%20a%20tenant%20out%2C%20from%20unpaid%20rent%20to%20simply%20not%20getting%20along.%20Even%20if%20their%20reasons%20are%20legitimate%2C%20landlords%20in%20most%20jurisdictions%20are%20required%20to%20go%20to%20court%20to%20seek%20an%20eviction%20and%20provide%20a%20tenant%20with%20notice%20of%20the%20eviction%20filing.%20Bypassing%20that%20system%20is%20illegal%20in%20most%20states%2C%20whether%20the%20landlord's%20grievance%20is%20justified%20or%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20due%20process%20in%20a%20lockout%20means%20someone%20like%20Perry%20never%20gets%20to%20show%20a%20judge%20his%20rent%20was%20paid%20up%20or%20prove%20that%20he'd%20followed%20the%20rules%20of%20his%20lease.%20And%20the%20lack%20of%20notice%20robs%20tenants%20of%20a%20window%20in%20which%20to%20line%20up%20alternative%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Perry's%20case%2C%20Wright%20claimed%20that%20Perry%20left%20voluntarily%2C%20with%20his%20possessions.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20the%20laws%20%E2%80%94%20I%20don't%20mess%20with%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Wright%20has%20a%20history%20of%20wrongful%20evictions%2C%20according%20to%20documents%20from%20the%20Las%20Vegas%20Justice%20Court%3A%20In%202022%2C%20his%20LLC%20was%20ordered%20to%20pay%20back%20nearly%20%24900%20for%20turning%20off%20the%20electricity%20on%20another%20tenant%20in%20Perry's%20building%2C%20and%20in%202020%2C%20he%20was%20ordered%20to%20restore%20access%20to%20a%20renter%20at%20another%20property%20after%20a%20judge%20found%20he'd%20illegally%20removed%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%202022%20case%2C%20Wright%20said%20one%20of%20his%20employees%20got%20%26quot%3Boverzealous%26quot%3B%3B%20of%20the%20other%20case%2C%20he%20said%20he'd%20tried%20to%20let%20the%20tenant%20back%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20because%20tenants%20file%20something%2C%20it%20doesn't%20mean%20something%20is%20true%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20judge%20never%20decided%20who%20was%20right%20in%20Perry's%20case.%20His%20complaint%20was%20tossed%20on%20a%20technicality.%20He'd%20missed%20the%20window%20to%20file.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETenants%20and%20their%20advocates%20say%20lockouts%20are%20extraordinarily%20disruptive.%20People%20often%20miss%20days%20of%20work%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnlihc.org%2Fresource%2Fhousing-instability-increases-likelihood-job-loss%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elose%20their%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20they%20prioritize%20finding%20somewhere%20to%20stay.%20Children%20fall%20behind%20academically%20or%20have%20to%20leave%20school%20altogether.%20Losing%20everything%20means%20starting%20from%20scratch%2C%20straining%20savings%20to%20pay%20for%20motels%20or%20to%20replace%20furniture%2C%20clothing%2C%20or%20medications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20such%20a%20traumatic%20thing%20for%20a%20family%20to%20be%20locked%20out%20without%20warning%2C%26quot%3B%20Charlie%20Bliss%2C%20the%20director%20of%20advocacy%20at%20Atlanta%20Legal%20Aid%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20real%20bunch%20of%20trouble.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'I'm%20sick%20of%20calling%20the%20cops'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELockouts%20largely%20happen%20out%20of%20public%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20research%20shows%20they%20may%20be%20widespread.%20In%202015%20a%20Princeton%20sociology%20professor%2C%20Matthew%20Desmond%2C%20surveyed%20Milwaukee%20tenants%20and%20found%20a%20ratio%20of%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.harvard.edu%2Ffiles%2Fmdesmond%2Ffiles%2Fdesmondshollenberger.demography.2015.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einformal%20forced%20removals%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20every%20one%20where%20landlords%20went%20through%20a%20formal%20court%20process%20and%20got%20a%20judge's%20eviction%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20piece%20together%20how%20often%20lockouts%20occur%2C%20BI%20sought%20records%20left%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20these%20illegal%20eviction%20attempts%20from%20police%20departments%20and%20housing%20agencies%20in%20eight%20large%20cities%20that%20have%20a%20high%20proportion%20of%20renters%20or%20tight%20housing%20markets%2C%20including%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20Chicago%2C%20Atlanta%2C%20and%20Las%20Vegas.%20We%20obtained%20911%20call%20logs%20and%20audio%2C%20police%20reports%2C%20bodycam%20footage%2C%20arrest%20data%2C%20and%20housing%20complaints.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELockouts%20briefly%20gained%20visibility%20during%20the%20coronavirus%20pandemic%2C%20as%20landlords%20sought%20to%20bypass%20a%20federal%20moratorium%20on%20evictions.%20But%20the%20expiration%20of%20the%20moratorium%20has%20not%20resulted%20in%20the%20abandonment%20of%20these%20illegal%20tactics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20investigation%20unearthed%20hundreds%20of%20cases%20in%20which%20data%20shows%20that%20the%20police%20did%20little%20to%20nothing%20when%20answering%20emergency%20calls%20for%20help%20with%20an%20illegal%20eviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20landlords%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flandlord-illegal-lockout-court-tenant-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erarely%20faced%20consequences%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20South%20Chicago%2C%20a%20landlord%20was%20ticketed%20for%20changing%20the%20locks%20on%20a%20tenant%20in%20January%202023%3B%20the%20ticket%20was%20tossed%20and%20he%20was%20let%20go%20with%20a%20verbal%20warning.%20On%20Christmas%20Day%202022%20in%20Phoenix%2C%20a%20woman%20who%20called%20911%20said%20her%20landlord%20was%20hooking%20up%20her%20trailer%20to%20his%20red%20Chevy%20truck%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20evict%20her.%20When%20the%20police%20called%20her%20back%20two%20hours%20later%2C%20they%20couldn't%20reach%20her.%20The%20incident%20was%20closed%20as%20%26quot%3Bno%20action%20required.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FEkFGl%2F8%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Landlords%20are%20rarely%20penalized%20for%20illegal%20lockouts%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22798%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F4Kr3C%2F16%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22CHICAGO%20NEW%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22792%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E911%20records%20from%20the%20winter%20of%202022-2023%20indicate%20that%20a%20pregnant%20woman%20in%20Jersey%20City's%20McGinley%20Square%20neighborhood%20was%20locked%20out%20of%20her%20apartment%20for%20five%20days.%20She%20said%20she%20was%20stuck%20doubled%20up%20with%20her%20grandmother%20in%20a%20local%20YMCA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20sick%20of%20calling%20the%20cops%20and%20nobody%20doing%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20tells%20a%20911%20dispatcher%2C%20frustrated%20after%20describing%20her%20situation%20multiple%20times%20to%20different%20police%20officers%20and%20call%20takers.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20freezing%2C%20I%20haven't%20took%20my%20prenatals%20in%20days%2C%20changed%20my%20clothes%20in%20days.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20she%20called%20911%20about%20being%20locked%20out%2C%20her%20landlord%20said%20it%20was%20because%20he%20did%20not%20want%20her%20dog%20in%20the%20house.%20He%20sat%20in%20the%20entrance%20to%20the%20apartment%2C%20undeterred%20by%20police%20officers%20telling%20him%20he%20could%20be%20arrested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELockouts%20are%20a%20crime%20in%20New%20Jersey.%20But%20the%20officers%20didn't%20arrest%20him%20or%20give%20him%20a%20citation%2C%20telling%20him%20to%20let%20the%20woman%20inside%20and%20take%20her%20to%20court.%20The%20landlord%20locked%20her%20out%20again%20two%20months%20later%20for%20four%20days%2C%20she%20reported%20to%20911.%20A%20different%20pair%20of%20officers%20responded%3B%20bodycam%20footage%20shows%20them%20trying%20to%20reach%20the%20landlord%20by%20phone%20after%20the%20tenant%20says%20he's%20blocked%20her%20number.%20Then%2C%20they%20tell%20her%20to%20get%20a%20locksmith.%20She%20called%20911%20again%20not%20long%20after%2C%20saying%20the%20locksmith%20had%20asked%20for%20cash%20but%20her%20cash%20was%20locked%20inside%20her%20apartment.%20It%20was%20a%20Catch-22.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBodycam%20footage%20shows%20an%20officer%20again%20trying%20to%20call%20the%20landlord%2C%20but%20the%20call%20goes%20straight%20to%20voicemail.%20One%20of%20the%20responding%20officers%20calls%20a%20sergeant%20over%2C%20who%20says%20there's%20nothing%20else%20they%20can%20do.%20Jersey%20City%20officials%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20she%20breaks%20back%20into%20her%20own%20home%2C%20the%20sergeant%20says%2C%20she'll%20shoulder%20the%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20advising%20against%20it%2C%20but%20you're%20a%20grown%20woman%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20officer%20tells%20her.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20you%20do%20is%20what%20you%20do%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20on%20you.%26quot%3B%20Meanwhile%2C%20with%20her%20uniform%20locked%20inside%2C%20the%20Jersey%20City%20woman%20says%20she%20missed%20days%20of%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELockout%20calls%20on%20the%20rise%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Jersey%20City%2C%20where%20a%20residential%20lockout%20can%20result%20in%20a%20criminal%20misdemeanor%2C%20a%20city%20clerk%20said%20he%20would%20be%20surprised%20if%20more%20than%20a%20handful%20of%20tenants%20had%20called%20911%20over%20an%20illegal%20lockout.%20In%20response%20to%20a%20records%20request%2C%20the%20same%20city%20clerk%20later%20identified%2090%20emergency%20calls%20alleging%20illegal%20evictions%20in%202021%20and%202022.%20In%20Atlanta%2C%20a%20public-information%20officer%20at%20the%20Atlanta%20Police%20Department%20said%20officers%20did%20not%20get%20involved%20in%20such%20cases%20and%20initially%20identified%20only%2013%20calls%20over%20three%20years%20in%20response%20to%20a%20freedom%20of%20information%20request.%20They%20later%20found%20more%20than%202%2C000%20such%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Atlanta%20police%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20subsequent%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20cities%20we%20examined%2C%20only%20Chicago%20dispatchers%20had%20a%20specific%20label%20for%20911%20calls%20reporting%20an%20illegal%20lockout%20%E2%80%94%20a%20code%20that%20was%20introduced%20recently%2C%20in%202021.%20Some%20departments%20had%20categories%20for%20landlord-tenant%20issues%2C%20while%20others%20lumped%20calls%20about%20wrongful%20evictions%20under%20umbrella%20terms%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Bdisturbance.%26quot%3B%20A%20few%20cities%20had%20no%20relevant%20categories%20at%20all.%20In%20these%20cities%2C%20BI%20requested%20service%20calls%20to%20911%20filtered%20by%20keywords%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Block%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bshut%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Blandlord%26quot%3B%20dating%20back%20to%20at%20least%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20excluded%20calls%20with%20sufficient%20information%20to%20show%20they%20were%20not%20pertinent%20to%20a%20lockout.%20The%20analysis%20shows%20that%20calls%20to%20the%20police%20for%20help%20regarding%20illegal%20evictions%20haven't%20fallen%20since%20the%20federal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F08%2F26%2Fus%2Feviction-moratorium-ends.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECOVID%20eviction%20moratorium%20was%20halted%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20response%20to%20a%20challenge%20by%20landlords%2C%20in%20August%202021.%20Instead%20they%20have%20roughly%20held%20steady%20or%20increased.%20In%20Atlanta%2C%20the%20volume%20of%20these%20calls%20rose%20each%20year%20from%202020%20to%202022.%20And%20in%20Houston%2C%20calls%20mentioning%20lockout%20keywords%20went%20up%20from%202021%20to%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETallies%20based%20on%20police%20calls%20are%20likely%20an%20undercount%2C%20tenant%20advocates%20say.%20Some%20renters%20don't%20know%20lockouts%20are%20illegal%3B%20others%20are%20hesitant%20to%20call%20the%20police%20or%20report%20an%20illegal%20eviction%20to%20the%20city%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons%2C%20including%20distrust%20of%20the%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20other%20agencies%20showed%20a%20similar%20increase.%20BI%20examined%20more%20than%2041%2C000%20housing%20complaints%20from%202020%20through%202023%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Housing%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20kinds%20of%20complaints%20cited%20by%20city%20council%20members%20in%202021%20when%20passing%20an%20ordinance%20to%20prohibit%20landlords%20from%20using%20harassment%20and%20coercion%20to%20force%20out%20tenants.%20We%20found%20that%20these%20complaints%20rose%2071%25%20from%202020%20to%202023.%20The%20volume%20of%20housing%20complaints%20illustrates%20how%20difficult%20it%20can%20be%20to%20track%20off-the-book%20evictions.%20For%202022%2C%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20Police%20Department%20turned%20over%20about%201%2C000%20calls%20made%20to%20the%20police%20with%20keywords%20related%20to%20illegal%20lockouts%20or%20utility%20shutoffs.%20For%20the%20same%20year%2C%20complaints%20to%20the%20housing%20department%20totaled%20more%20than%2011%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F7GZB4%2F3%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Locked%20out%3F%20What%20you%20can%20do%20varies%20widely%20by%20state.%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22573%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Nevada%2C%20a%20state%20law%20lets%20tenants%20who%20were%20wrongfully%20evicted%20sue%20their%20landlord%20to%20get%20back%20into%20their%20unit.%20The%20number%20of%20such%20cases%20in%20one%20Las%20Vegas%20courts%20has%20modestly%20increased%20year%20over%20year%2C%20rising%20from%20300%20cases%20filed%20in%202020%20to%20353%20in%202023.%20Texas%20has%20a%20similar%20law.%20In%20Harris%20County%2C%20petitions%20over%20lockouts%20and%20utility%20shutoffs%20%E2%80%94%20mostly%20from%20Houston%20%E2%80%94%20nearly%20doubled%20from%202019%20to%202023%2C%20data%20shows%2C%20going%20from%2088%20cases%20to%20153.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Leibowitz%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Arizona%20Multi-Housing%20Association%2C%20a%20group%20representing%20landlords%20and%20management%20companies%2C%20said%20that%20while%20the%20association%20does%20not%20condone%20self-help%20evictions%20%E2%80%94%20another%20term%20for%20a%20lockout%20%E2%80%94%20he%20didn't%20know%20whether%20the%20problem%20is%20pervasive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20call%20the%20police%20for%20all%20sorts%20of%20reasons%2C%26quot%3B%20Leibowitz%20said.%20%26quot%3BStatistics%20are%20hard%20to%20come%20by%20in%20the%20legal%20circumstances%20%E2%80%94%20now%20you're%20talking%20about%20these%20illegal%20situations%20and%20it's%20even%20harder.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELockouts%20by%20corporate%20landlords%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAdvocates%20for%20both%20landlords%20and%20tenants%20say%2C%20in%20their%20experience%2C%20unsophisticated%20mom-and-pop%20landlords%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20lock%20out%20their%20tenants.%20Buoyed%20by%20low%20interest%20rates%20in%202021%2C%20many%20new%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20perhaps%20unfamiliar%20with%20landlord-tenant%20law%20%E2%80%94%20purchased%20apartment%20buildings%2C%20only%20to%20find%20that%20profits%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fonce-ironclad-apartments-buildings-could-now-see-defaults-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehad%20not%20kept%20up%20with%20debt%20obligations%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20the%20cost%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fa-housing-bust-comes-for-thousands-of-small-time-investors-3934beb3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregular%20maintenance%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20aggressive%20tactics%20to%20remove%20a%20resident%20are%20not%20confined%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouthern-towers-apartment-tenants-battle-investor-landlord-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmall%20landlords%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20may%20lack%20familiarity%20with%20the%20law.%20A%20congressional%20investigation%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcoronavirus-democrats-oversight.house.gov%2Fsites%2Fevo-subsites%2Fcoronavirus-democrats-oversight.house.gov%2Ffiles%2F2022.07.28%2520SSCC%2520Staff%2520Report%2520Examining%2520Pandemic%2520Evictions.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efour%20major%20corporate%20landlords%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20July%202022%20found%20that%20they%20had%20collectively%20filed%20more%20than%2014%2C000%20evictions%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20despite%20a%20federal%20eviction%20moratorium.%20The%20investigators%20describe%20the%20eviction%20filings%20as%20%26quot%3Baggressive%26quot%3B%20but%20not%20unlawful.%20Spokespeople%20for%20two%20of%20the%20landlords%20named%20in%20the%20report%20%E2%80%94%20Invitation%20Homes%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpretium.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPretium%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20reiterated%20the%20latter%20finding%20in%20response%20to%20BI's%20queries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Kristi%20DesJarlais%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.invitationhomes.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInvitation%20Homes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20took%20issue%20with%20the%20characterization%20of%20the%20company's%20practices%20as%20aggressive.%20Words%20like%20that%20are%20not%20%26quot%3Baccurate%20words%20to%20describe%20a%20company%20following%20a%20legal%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20by%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20investigators%20also%20found%20evidence%20that%20one%20of%20the%20companies%2C%20The%20Siegel%20Group%2C%20had%20engaged%20in%20%26quot%3Bpotentially%20unlawful%20practices%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20instructing%20managers%20to%20threaten%20residents%20with%20calls%20to%20Child%20Protective%20Services%2C%20replace%20a%20functioning%20air-conditioning%20unit%20with%20a%20broken%20one%2C%20or%20threaten%20to%20tow%20their%20car%20to%20get%20them%20to%20move%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECounsel%20for%20The%20Siegel%20Group%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20investment%20firm%20that%20services%20multifamily%20units%20and%20extended-stay%20apartments%20in%20several%20Western%20states%2C%20confirmed%20in%20an%20email%20to%20the%20congressional%20subcommittee%20leading%20the%20investigation%20that%20the%20company%20used%20lockouts%20instead%20of%20evictions%20in%20some%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22786%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tearsheet%20from%20a%20Congressional%20subcommittee%20report%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667d7bd740cf2af6e4f634a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22404%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20July%202022%20report%20on%20pandemic%20evictions%20from%20a%20congressional%20subcommittee%20singled%20out%20The%20Siegel%20Group%20as%20deploying%20potentially%20extralegal%20tactics.%20Siegel%20has%20disputed%20some%20of%20the%20committee's%20findings.%3Cp%3EUS%20Congress%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESean%20Thueson%2C%20the%20general%20counsel%20for%20The%20Siegel%20Group%2C%20said%20the%20company's%20email%20only%20confirmed%20lockouts%20were%20used%20at%20hotels%20or%20motels%20%26quot%3Bunder%20state%20law%20that%20specifically%20authorize%20lock%20outs%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20%26quot%3Beach%20individual%20property%20handles%20its%20own%20lock%20outs%20%2F%20evictions%20and%20follows%20the%20laws%20of%20the%20specific%20state.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20specific%20cases%20in%20which%20tenants%20were%20granted%20judgments%20after%20wrongful%20evictions%20in%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20Thueson%20said%20that%20The%20Siegel%20Group%20had%20been%20improperly%20named%20and%20bore%20no%20responsibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20BI%20found%20more%20than%20one%20in%20three%20landlords%20facing%20illegal-lockout%20claims%20are%20companies%2C%20including%20The%20Siegel%20Group%20and%20such%20major%20players%20as%20Progress%20Residential%2C%20the%20largest%20corporate%20landlord%20in%20the%20Nevada%20county%20and%20a%20subsidiary%20of%20the%20investment%20firm%20Pretium%2C%20and%20Invitation%20Homes%2C%20the%20single-family%20rental%20company%20founded%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblackstone-real-estate-tenant-concerns-landlord-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBlackstone%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(Blackstone%20sold%20off%20its%20remaining%20shares%20of%20the%20company%20in%202019.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20found%20a%20similar%20pattern%20in%20Harris%20County%2C%20home%20to%20Houston%2C%20where%20about%20one%20in%20three%20tenant%20filings%20alleging%20lockouts%20from%202019%20through%202023%20named%20corporate%20landlords%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frentprogress.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProgress%20Residential%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(Some%20related%20to%20commercial%20tenants.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20complaints%20against%20Invitation%20Homes%20and%20Progress%20Residential%2C%20none%20were%20upheld%2C%20according%20to%20justice%20courts%20in%20Texas%20and%20Nevada%2C%20whether%20because%20the%20lockouts%20were%20deemed%20legal%2C%20because%20no%20one%20showed%20up%20to%20a%20hearing%2C%20or%20because%20the%20tenant%20had%20been%20locked%20out%20by%20a%20family%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20no%20time%20has%20Invitation%20Homes%20ever%20evicted%20a%20resident%20without%20pursuing%20the%20action%20by%20legal%20means%20and%20obtaining%20a%20court%20order%2C%26quot%3B%20DesJarlais%20of%20Invitation%20Homes%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20cannot%20and%20will%20not%20unilaterally%20evict%20a%20resident%20from%20one%20of%20our%20homes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProgress%20Residential%20complied%20with%20applicable%20laws%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20company%20spokesperson%20said%20by%20email.%20%26quot%3BAny%20implication%20of%20the%20contrary%20is%20false.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20Minnesota's%20attorney%20general%20settled%20a%20lawsuit%20for%20%242.2%20million%20with%20Pretium%2C%20Progress%20Residential%2C%20and%20other%20related%20companies%20over%20chronic%20disrepair%20and%20illegally%20terminating%20people's%20tenancies%20at%20hundreds%20of%20single-family%20homes.%20While%20Pretium%20requested%20to%20be%20dismissed%20from%20the%20case%2C%20and%20denied%20any%20wrongdoing%2C%20Assistant%20Attorney%20General%20Katherine%20Kelly%20said%20there%20was%20no%20question%20Pretium%20was%20involved%20in%20the%20management%20of%20the%20units.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20knew%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20didn't%20stop%20it%2C%20they%20let%20it%20go%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorporate%20landlords%20have%20recently%20come%20under%20fire%20for%20other%20potentially%20illegal%20tactics.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20the%20past%20several%20months%2C%20attorneys%20general%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.azag.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-02%2FRealPage%2520Complaint.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArizona%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20have%20sued%20RealPage%20over%20claims%20it%20had%20assisted%20landlords%20in%20systematically%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapartment-rent-increases-landlords-antitrust-lawsuits-real-estate-software-realpage-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejacking%20up%20rents%3C%2Fa%3E%20above%20market%20price%2C%20an%20arrangement%20state%20officials%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foag.dc.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2023-11%2FDC%2520OAG%2520RealPage%2520Complaint%2520-%2520Filed.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edescribed%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Brent-setting%20cartel.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20lawsuits%20are%20wrong%20on%20both%20the%20facts%20and%20the%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20Jennifer%20Bowcock%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20RealPage%2C%20said%20by%20email.%20%26quot%3BThe%20complaints%20are%20based%20on%20a%20fundamental%20misunderstanding%20of%20how%20revenue%20management%20software%20works%20and%20the%20significant%20benefits%20that%20it%20offers%20for%20residents%2C%20property%20managers%2C%20and%20the%20rental%20housing%20ecosystem%20as%20a%20whole.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEnforcement%20failures%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20right%20to%20due%20process%20during%20an%20eviction%20is%20one%20of%20the%20country's%20oldest%20laws.%20Based%20on%20English%20criminal%20statutes%20that%20date%20back%20to%20the%201300s%2C%20some%20American%20colonies%20banned%20extrajudicial%20eviction%20tactics%20even%20before%20they%20formally%20joined%20the%20Union%2C%20considering%20violators%20a%20threat%20to%20public%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20as%20far%20back%20as%20the%2018th%20century%2C%20courts%20were%20involved%20in%20the%20adjudication%20of%20landlord-tenant%20disputes%20and%20tended%20not%20to%20support%20a%20tenant's%20immediate%20eviction%2C%20recognizing%20the%20hardship%20it%20would%20entail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFew%20things%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20lead%20to%20a%20brawl%20than%20an%20evicting%20landlord%2C%20throwing%20out%20his%20tenant%20by%20main%20force%2C%26quot%3B%20William%20Prosser%2C%20author%20of%20the%20seminal%20work%20%26quot%3BHandbook%20of%20the%20Law%20of%20Torts%2C%26quot%3B%20argued%20in%201941.%20%26quot%3BThe%20public%20interest%20in%20preserving%20the%20peace%20would%20seem%20to%20justify%20the%20temporary%20inconvenience%20to%20the%20owner.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20however%2C%20illegal%20evictions%20are%20often%20left%20in%20the%20hands%20not%20of%20experienced%20judges%20but%20of%20undertrained%20police%20officers%20who%20sometimes%20abysmally%20fail%20to%20protect%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hud.gov%2Ftopics%2Frental_assistance%2Ftenantrights%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etenants'%20rights%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20four%20of%20the%20major%20metro%20areas%20BI%20examined%2C%20agencies%20explicitly%20direct%20tenants%20to%20call%20the%20police%20if%20they're%20locked%20out.%20So%20does%20guidance%20for%20New%20Jersey's%20superior%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20which%20is%20governed%20by%20a%20state%20directive%20encouraging%20law%20enforcement%20to%20treat%20lockouts%20as%20a%20criminal%20offense%2C%20the%20city's%20Housing%20Department%20website%20instructs%20tenants%20to%20%26quot%3Bcall%20the%20local%20police%20at%20the%20closest%20precinct%20to%20help%20with%20re-entry.%26quot%3B%20Welcoming%20Atlanta%2C%20a%20program%20of%20the%20mayor's%20office%20in%20Atlanta%2C%20where%20police%20typically%20treat%20lockouts%20as%20civil%20matters%2C%20directs%20people%20to%20%26quot%3Bcall%20your%20non%20emergency%20police%20line%20and%20report%20them%20as%20a%20trespasser%2C%26quot%3B%20referring%20to%20the%20landlord.%20%26quot%3BThe%20police%20officer%20should%20tell%20them%20that%20they%20must%20leave%20the%20property%20or%20face%20charges%20for%20criminal%20trespass.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20in%20places%20where%20the%20police%20are%20clearly%20responsible%20for%20responding%20to%20an%20illegal%20eviction%20and%20taking%20action%20against%20the%20landlord%2C%20many%20officers%20choose%20not%20to%20get%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F1kZnV%2F5%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Police%20reports%20are%20rare%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22310%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20cities%20across%20the%20nation%2C%20calls%20about%20a%20lockout%20very%20rarely%20lead%20to%20a%20police%20report%2C%20BI's%20analysis%20shows.%20For%20the%20rest%2C%20officers%20took%20some%20other%20course%20of%20action%2C%20whether%20persuading%20landlords%20to%20let%20a%20tenant%20back%20in%2C%20referring%20the%20tenant%20or%20landlord%20to%20another%20agency%20%E2%80%94%20or%20simply%20leaving%20landlords%20off%20the%20hook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20reviewed%208%2C268%20911%20calls%20about%20lockouts%20received%20as%20far%20back%20as%202020%20in%20four%20cities%20%E2%80%94%20Chicago%2C%20Houston%2C%20Atlanta%2C%20and%20Miami%20%E2%80%94%20that%20included%20information%20on%20how%20police%20departments%20resolved%20them.%20BI%20also%20analyzed%20data%20on%20911%20calls%20in%20Phoenix%20from%20January%202020%20through%202023%20coded%20simply%20as%20landlord-tenant%20disputes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%203%2C600%20calls%20to%20the%20police%20in%20Chicago%20from%20February%202021%20to%20July%202023%2C%2017%25%20led%20to%20a%20police%20report.%20Police%20officers%20filed%20even%20fewer%20reports%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Phoenix%2C%20where%20lockouts%20are%20civil%20violations%2C%20most%20landlord-tenant%20911%20calls%20were%20tagged%20as%20%26quot%3Bno%20action%20required%26quot%3B%20and%20only%2014%25%20led%20to%20a%20police%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAtlanta%2C%20Miami%2C%20and%20Houston%20were%20in%20the%20single%20digits.%20In%20Atlanta%2C%209%25%20of%20lockout%20calls%20from%20January%202020%20through%20early%202023%20ended%20in%20a%20police%20report.%20Houston%20police%20officers%20wrote%20reports%20after%20only%208%25%20of%20calls%20from%202021%20to%20early%202023.%20And%20Miami%20police%20officers%20wrote%20reports%20for%208%25%20of%20calls%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolice%20departments%20in%20Atlanta%2C%20Miami%2C%20and%20Chicago%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20detailed%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Houston%20Police%20Department%20issued%20a%20statement%20saying%20officers%20were%20trained%20in%20identifying%20criminal%20versus%20civil%20matters%20and%20officers%20were%20guided%20not%20to%20enforce%20the%20latter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Phoenix%20police%20spokesperson%2C%20Donna%20Rossi%2C%20said%20by%20email%20that%20calls%20about%20lockouts%20%26quot%3Bcould%20refer%20to%20both%20legal%20and%20non-legal%20situations%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Bpolice%20involvement%20would%20end%20if%20no%20crime%20has%20been%20committed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20reports%20stands%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20with%20enforcement%20of%20other%2C%20often%20less%20consequential%2C%20property%20crimes%20like%20shoplifting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F34j9z%2F8%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Fewer%20arrests%20for%20lockouts%20than%20other%20property%20crimes%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22227%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EPolice%20data%20from%20the%20start%20of%202020%20through%20the%20end%20of%202023%20in%20Phoenix%20shows%20an%20inverse%20ratio.%20While%20only%2014%25%20of%20lockout%20calls%20led%20to%20a%20police%20report%2C%2086%25%20of%20calls%20about%20shoplifting%20did.%20The%20Council%20on%20Criminal%20Justice%20has%20found%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounciloncj.org%2Fshoplifting-trends-what-you-need-to-know%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520median%2520value%2520of%2520goods%2Ca%2520%2524184%2520increase%2520from%25202019.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emedian%20cost%20of%20shoplifted%20goods%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%20was%20%24100.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20Chicago%20and%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20where%20the%20police%20are%20explicitly%20mandated%20to%20stop%20illegal%20evictions%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0up%20to%20and%20including%20making%20an%20arrest%20%E2%80%94%20BI%20found%20a%20similar%20pattern.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%202020%20through%20the%20end%20of%202023%2C%20Chicago%20police%20officers%20made%20eight%20arrests%20of%20landlords%20accused%20of%20illegally%20locking%20out%20tenants.%20By%20comparison%2C%20they%20made%20more%20than%206%2C300%20arrests%20of%20people%20suspected%20of%20shoplifting%20merchandise%20worth%20less%20than%20%24300%20over%20the%20same%20time%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221004%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20ticket%20given%20to%20a%20landlord%20by%20the%20Chicago%20police%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667d7bd740cf2af6e4f634a5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221066%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20police%20ticketed%20a%20Chicago%20landlord%20in%20April%202023%20for%20%26quot%3Bleaving%20a%20tenant%20with%20no%20power.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EChicago%20Department%20of%20Administrative%20Hearings%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20it's%20illegal%20to%20steal%20a%20candy%20bar%20from%20a%20store%2C%20why%20is%20there%20seemingly%20no%20consequence%20for%20turning%20someone's%20heat%20off%3F%26quot%3B%20said%20Sara%20Heymann%2C%20a%20community%20organizer%20in%20Chicago%20who%20advocates%20on%20behalf%20of%20tenants%20who%20are%20experiencing%20a%20lockout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20California%20issued%20guidance%20directing%20law-enforcement%20agencies%20to%20treat%20illegal%20eviction%20as%20a%20crime%2C%20police%20officers%20rarely%20make%20arrests%2C%20according%20to%20LAPD%20arrest%20data.%20BI%20tallied%20more%20than%2041%2C000%20housing%20complaints%20%E2%80%94%20which%20can%20range%20from%20landlords%20giving%20insufficient%20notice%20in%20the%20course%20of%20a%20formal%20eviction%20process%20to%20landlords%20locking%20tenants%20out%20or%20cutting%20off%20utilities%20%E2%80%94%20from%20January%202020%20through%20the%20end%20of%202023%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%20Yet%20over%20the%20same%20time%20period%2C%20the%20LAPD%20arrested%20only%20six%20people%20under%20the%20main%20statute%20cited%20by%20the%20attorney%20general%20as%20having%20to%20do%20with%20an%20illegal%20eviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thecity.nyc%2F2022%2F02%2F17%2Fnyc-landlords-illegal-evictions-arrests%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestigation%20by%20The%20City%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20this%20pattern%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20where%20the%20NYPD%20made%20just%2039%20lockout%20arrests%20in%202020%20and%202021%20out%20of%20more%20than%202%2C600%20complaints.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20respond%20to%20the%20calls%20as%20best%20we%20can%20if%20it's%20within%20what%20we%20can%20enforce%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20LAPD%20spokesperson%2C%20Detective%20Meghan%20Aguilar%2C%20told%20BI%2C%20but%20she%20declined%20to%20answer%20questions%20about%20the%20department's%20training%20on%20responding%20to%20lockout%20calls%20and%20its%20enforcement%20of%20criminal%20laws%20banning%20lockouts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'What's%20your%20plan%20for%20tonight%3F'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERecords%20show%20relying%20on%20the%20police%20for%20help%20on%20lockouts%20is%20a%20gamble.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20bodycam%20footage%20BI%20obtained%20of%20police%20responses%20to%20911%20calls%20about%20illegal%20evictions%2C%20officers'%20behavior%20appears%20almost%20improvised.%20Some%20recognize%20a%20lockout%20as%20illegal%20and%20direct%20landlords%20to%20the%20courts%20for%20a%20lawful%20eviction.%20But%20others%20don't%20appear%20to%20know%20the%20law%2C%20even%20in%20states%20where%20the%20police%20are%20tasked%20to%20uphold%20it.%20Some%20resort%20to%20searching%20the%20internet%20for%20guidance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20Jersey%20City%20incident%20in%20December%202022%2C%20a%20police%20officer%20appears%20to%20misunderstand%20a%20judge's%20order%20%26quot%3Bstaying%26quot%3B%20a%20lockout%20%E2%80%94%20a%20decision%20that%20the%20eviction%20may%20not%20be%20enforced%20%E2%80%94%20as%20meaning%20the%20tenant%20should%20%26quot%3Bstay%26quot%3B%20locked%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2FsV79S4C9-puACk8ZV.html%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Body%20Cam%201%20%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20February%202023%20case%20there%2C%20a%20baffled%20tenant%20asks%20officers%20responding%20to%20her%20911%20call%20whether%20her%20landlord%20could%20legally%20lock%20her%20out%3A%20Yes%2C%20they%20can%2C%20the%20officer%20wrongly%20says.%20New%20Jersey%20law%20states%20that%20even%20after%20a%20legal%20eviction%20is%20granted%20by%20a%20judge%2C%20only%20a%20court%20officer%20can%20remove%20the%20tenant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETenants'%20outcomes%20vary%20dramatically%20according%20to%20which%20officers%20happen%20to%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20two%20separate%20instances%20in%202021%20and%202022%2C%20the%20Jersey%20City%20police%20conducted%20criminal%20investigations%20into%20landlords%20accused%20of%20locking%20out%20tenants%20or%20shutting%20off%20their%20utilities.%20In%20one%20case%2C%20a%20landlord%20cut%20the%20building's%20electrical%20wiring%2C%20leaving%20multiple%20families%20without%20power%2C%20heat%2C%20or%20fire%20protection%20for%20days.%20He%20received%20two%20court%20summons%20for%20the%20offenses.%20In%20the%20other%2C%20a%20woman%20said%20she%20came%20home%20to%20a%20padlock%20on%20her%20door%20and%20about%20%2410%2C000%20in%20missing%20property%2C%20including%20clothing%20and%20appliances.%20But%20the%20police%20could%20find%20no%20record%20of%20an%20arrest%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2F4wJZzrqB-puACk8ZV.html%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Body%20Cam%202%20%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20landlords%20were%20let%20off%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202023%2C%20a%20woman%20identified%20as%20Misty%20Skinner%20called%20the%20Las%20Vegas%20Metropolitan%20Police%20Department%20after%20she%20and%20her%20daughter%20were%20locked%20out%20of%20their%20home%20in%20Spring%20Valley%2C%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Las%20Vegas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWearing%20only%20a%20fleece%20jacket%20on%20a%20day%20with%20a%20low%20temperature%20of%2034%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%2C%20bodycam%20footage%20shows%20Skinner%20telling%20police%20officers%20her%20landlord%20demanded%20they%20leave%20within%2024%20hours.%20Scared%2C%20she%20and%20her%20daughter%20left%2C%20she%20says%2C%20but%20now%20they%20can't%20reach%20the%20landlord%20to%20arrange%20to%20gather%20their%20belongings%2C%20including%20her%20daughter's%20nebulizer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Blurry%20body%20cam%20footage%20of%20a%20woman%20in%20a%20blue%20sweatshirt%20standing%20outside%20her%20home%20in%20the%20dark%20next%20to%20a%20child%20in%20a%20black%20hoodie.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666b6c6e764df1611259ca79%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221497%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPolice%20bodycam%20footage%20captures%20the%20night%20Misty%20Skinner%20and%20her%20daughter%20were%20locked%20out%20of%20their%20home%20in%20Spring%20Valley%2C%20Nevada%2C%20in%20January%202023%20as%20temperatures%20neared%20freezing.%3Cp%3ELas%20Vegas%20Metropolitan%20Police%20Department%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20your%20plan%20for%20tonight%3F%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20the%20officers%20asks%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20a%20plan%20%E2%80%94%20this%20is%20our%20plan.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDo%20you%20have%20a%20car%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%2C%20I%20do%20not%2C%20or%20we%20would%20be%20in%20our%20car%2C%20waiting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDo%20you%20have%20money%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20money%2C%20'cause%20we%20spent%20our%20money%20for%20two%20nights%20on%20a%20B%26amp%3BB.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESkinner%20says%20her%20landlord%2C%20Levi%20Wilhelm%2C%20lives%20next%20door.%20As%20they%20walk%20over%2C%20one%20of%20the%20officers%20tells%20the%20other%20to%20look%20up%20%26quot%3Billegal%20lockout%26quot%3B%20on%20his%20phone.%20In%20the%20footage%2C%20lights%20are%20on%20in%20the%20house%20and%20cars%20are%20in%20the%20driveway.%20But%20there%20is%20no%20response%20when%20officers%20knock%20on%20his%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20gonna%20be%20on%20her%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20the%20police%20officers%20says%20to%20his%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20what%20do%20we%20do%20now%3F%26quot%3B%20Skinner%20says%2C%20her%20voice%20breaking.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20right.%20It's%20not%20fair.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDo%20you%20have%20any%20friends%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20anybody%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20wiping%20tears%20from%20her%20cheek.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20officers%20say%20that%20since%20she%20hasn't%20been%20formally%20evicted%2C%20they%20won't%20arrest%20her%20if%20she%20breaks%20back%20in%2C%20say%2C%20with%20a%20rock.%20%26quot%3BI've%20had%20these%20before%20where%20we've%20actually%20supplied%20them%20crowbars%20from%20the%20tac%20vehicle%20to%20get%20inside%20their%20homes%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20officer%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20officers%20think%20better%20of%20her%20breaking%20in%2C%20expressing%20concern%20that%20Wilhelm%20could%20return%20and%20become%20violent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20approach%20two%20neighbors%20to%20ask%20whether%20they'd%20let%20Skinner%20and%20her%20daughter%20come%20inside%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20hours.%20When%20the%20neighbors%20refuse%2C%20the%20officers%20advise%20Skinner%20to%20head%20to%20a%20gas%20station%20to%20warm%20up%20and%20give%20her%20a%20card%20to%20document%20the%20incident.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flandlord-illegal-lockout-court-tenant-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENevada%20has%20a%20procedure%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20let%20tenants%20back%20into%20their%20homes%20quickly%20in%20the%20event%20of%20an%20illegal%20lockout%2C%20but%20police%20officers%20direct%20her%20to%20the%20wrong%20agency.%20Records%20show%20the%20incident%20was%20closed%20that%20same%20night%20without%20a%20police%20report.%20Wilhelm%20filed%20an%20eviction%20with%20the%20courts%2010%20days%20later.%20He%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20calls%20and%20emails%20requesting%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2FtfT9zlk2-puACk8ZV.html%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Body%20Cam%203%20%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20bodycam%20footage%20of%20another%20lockout%20call%20four%20months%20earlier%2C%20a%20different%20pair%20of%20officers%20respond.%20This%20time%2C%20the%20officers%20coach%20the%20tenant%20on%20how%20to%20break%20down%20his%20door%20and%20stand%20by%20as%20he%20does%20it.%20The%20Las%20Vegas%20Metro%20Police%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolice%20training%20materials%20from%20multiple%20departments%20describe%20their%20role%20as%20keepers%20of%20the%20peace%20during%20a%20lockout%2C%20rather%20than%20enforcers%20of%20the%20law.%20In%20the%20early%20months%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20a%20group%20of%20housing%20activists%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20began%20to%20break%20tenants%20back%20into%20their%20homes%20before%20calling%20the%20police%2C%20since%20they'd%20noticed%20that%20whoever%20is%20inside%20the%20residence%20when%20the%20police%20show%20up%20is%20often%20the%20party%20who%20will%20stay%20inside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFolks%20are%20left%20to%20their%20own%20devices%20as%20far%20as%20getting%20themselves%20back%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Jeffrey%20Uno%2C%20managing%20attorney%20for%20the%20eviction-defense%20center%20at%20the%20Legal%20Aid%20Foundation%20of%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20punishments%20on%20paper%2C%20but%20in%20reality%2C%20they're%20being%20ignored.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETraining%20failures%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20found%20training%20for%20police%20officers%20on%20how%20to%20respond%20to%20a%20lockout%20is%20spotty.%20Some%20departments%2C%20such%20as%20Miami's%2C%20said%20they%20didn't%20have%20any%20training%20materials%20on%20lockouts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20officers%20are%20trained%20on%20how%20to%20identify%20a%20squatter%20and%20on%20the%20criminal%20charges%20for%20breaking%20into%20a%20vacant%20property%2C%20but%20the%20guidance%20makes%20no%20mention%20of%20the%20laws%20surrounding%20illegal%20lockouts%20or%20the%20remedies%20they%20can%20offer%20tenants.%20Other%20departments%20effectively%20direct%20cops%20to%20turn%20a%20blind%20eye.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Phoenix%20Police%20Department%20instructs%20officers%20to%20%26quot%3Bnot%20take%20enforcement%20action%26quot%3B%20after%20observing%20violations%20to%20the%20state's%20landlord-tenant%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Atlanta%20Police%20Department%20treats%20calls%20about%20evictions%20as%20civil%20matters%20and%20tells%20officers%20to%20%26quot%3Bnot%20render%20any%20aid%20or%20assistance%20in%20official%20capacity%20to%20either%20party%26quot%3B%20in%20civil%20disputes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Atlanta%20police%20declined%20an%20interview%20request%2C%20directing%20BI%20to%20the%20county%20marshal.%20Maj.%20Deirdre%20Orange%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Fulton%20County%20Marshal's%20Department%2C%20said%20marshals%20don't%20get%20involved%20in%20any%20eviction%20that%20isn't%20ordered%20by%20a%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Avondale%2C%20Arizona%2C%20a%20policy%20manual%20says%20cops%20are%20to%20%26quot%3Bpersuade%26quot%3B%20people%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20law%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20tenant-landlord%20violations%2C%20but%20not%20to%20make%20any%20arrests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Daniel%20Benavidez%2C%20a%20community%20resource%20officer%20with%20the%20Avondale%20Police%20Department%2C%20said%20officers%20are%20trained%20to%20identify%20criminal%20behavior%20when%20responding%20to%20these%20calls.%20%26quot%3BOne%20of%20our%20roles%20is%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20people%20are%20protected%20in%20their%20homes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20someone%20removes%20someone%20from%20a%20home%20without%20lawful%20authority%2C%20that%20would%20be%20kidnapping%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20clarified.%20%26quot%3BIt%20could%20be%20stealing%2C%20it%20could%20be%20criminal%20damage%2C%20it%20can%20be%20criminal%20impersonation%2C%20fraudulent%20scheme.%20It%20could%20be%20any%20type%20of%20crime.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20subsequent%20email%2C%20Sgt.%20Jenny%20Chavez%20said%20the%20department%20referred%20callers%20complaining%20of%20lockouts%20to%20the%20county%20constable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22902%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tearsheet%20from%20Avondale%20Police%20Department%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667d7bd7d1c84a0eaca842fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22390%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETraining%20for%20police%20officers%20on%20how%20to%20respond%20to%20a%20lockout%20is%20spotty.%20A%20police%20manual%20in%20Avondale%2C%20Arizona%2C%20says%20cops%20are%20to%20%26quot%3Bpersuade%26quot%3B%20people%20to%20comply%20with%20landlord-tenant%20law%20but%20not%20to%20make%20any%20arrests.%3Cp%3EAvondale%20Police%20Department%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20at%20least%20one%20case%2C%20police%20training%20openly%20undercuts%20state%20law-enforcement%20directives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202022%2C%20the%20California%20attorney%20general%20issued%20new%20guidelines%20on%20the%20illegality%20of%20lockouts%20to%20police%20departments%20and%20sheriffs%20statewide%2C%20directing%20officers%20to%20tell%20landlords%20to%20let%20tenants%20back%20into%20their%20homes.%20The%20state%20doesn't%20have%20a%20law%20explicitly%20criminalizing%20lockouts%2C%20but%20the%20bulletin%20emphasizes%20that%20lockouts%20violate%20other%20criminal%20laws%20and%20directs%20officers%20to%20%26quot%3Bintervene%20to%20enforce%20the%20law%20and%20stop%20self-help%20evictions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20an%20LAPD%20training%20bulletin%2C%20updated%20just%20two%20months%20after%20the%20AG%20bulletin%2C%20tells%20the%20police%20that%20while%20tenants%20behind%20on%20their%20rent%20will%20%26quot%3Bvery%20often%26quot%3B%20be%20locked%20out%20by%20their%20landlords%2C%20%26quot%3Bofficers%20lack%20the%20legal%20authority%20to%20demand%20that%20the%20landlord%20allow%20re-entry%20to%20the%20tenant.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20California's%20attorney%20general%2C%20Rob%20Bonta%2C%20did%20not%20make%20him%20available%20for%20an%20interview.%20The%20LAPD%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20its%20training%20bulletin%20in%20light%20of%20the%20AG's%20guidance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20one%20department%2C%20in%20Jersey%20City%2C%20turned%20over%20training%20materials%20that%20detail%20how%20to%20enforce%20lockout%20laws.%20BI%20separately%20obtained%20a%20Chicago%20police%20training%20video%2C%20in%20which%20Eric%20Carter%2C%20then%20the%20first%20deputy%20superintendent%2C%20lays%20out%20that%20the%20police%20department%20%26quot%3Bcan%20use%20its%20authority%20to%20compel%20landlords%20to%20end%20unlawful%20threats%20or%20actions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOfficers%20can%20and%20should%20respond%20to%20lockout%20complaints%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20Bartlett%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Metropolitan%20Tenants%20Organization%2C%20says%20in%20the%20video.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20common%20misunderstanding%20that%20lockouts%2C%20like%20most%20landlord%20and%20tenant%20disputes%2C%20are%20a%20civil%20matter%20in%20which%20the%20police%20cannot%20intervene.%20That%20is%20not%20the%20case.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBoth%20landlords%20and%20tenants%20are%20suffering%20through%20hard%20times%2C%20and%20the%20temptation%20to%20resort%20to%20unlawful%20threats%20and%20actions%20has%20never%20been%20greater%2C%26quot%3B%20Carter%20says%20in%20the%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20patchwork%20of%20laws%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EComplicating%20matters%20is%20a%20patchwork%20of%20disparate%20states%20laws%20governing%20what%20constitutes%20an%20illegal%20eviction%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20penalties%20for%20violating%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Arkansas%2C%20Georgia%2C%20Mississippi%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20and%20Wyoming%2C%20no%20laws%20are%20in%20place%20that%20explicitly%20ban%20lockouts.%20In%20Connecticut%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20Minnesota%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20and%20New%20York%2C%20lockouts%20are%20a%20crime%20carrying%20penalties%20of%20up%20to%20six%20months%20in%20jail%3B%20with%20the%20attorney%20general's%20directive%2C%20California%20became%20a%20sixth%20state%20with%20criminal%20penalties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222550%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20diagram%20from%20the%20Texas%20Justice%20Court%20tries%20to%20explain%20the%20convoluted%20process%20by%20which%20a%20locked-out%20tenant%20can%20seek%20a%20speedy%20order%20of%20reentry.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667d7bd7d1c84a0eaca842ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223300%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20diagram%20from%20the%20Texas%20Justice%20Court%20tries%20to%20explain%20the%20speedy%20but%20convoluted%20process%20by%20which%20a%20locked-out%20tenant%20can%20seek%20a%20speedy%20order%20of%20reentry.%3Cp%3ETexas%20Justice%20Court%20Training%20Center%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EState%20law%20in%20New%20Jersey%20establishes%20that%20even%20a%20landlord's%20verbal%20threats%20can%20be%20criminal.%20Delaware%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20one%20of%2039%20states%20with%20only%20civil%20penalties%20for%20lockouts%2C%20bans%20only%20landlords'%20removal%20or%20exclusion%20of%20tenants%20from%20their%20home%20without%20a%20court%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20within%20states%2C%20definitions%20vary%20on%20what%20constitutes%20an%20illegal%20eviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Illinois%20forbids%20landlords%20from%20tampering%20with%20utilities%2C%20the%20city%20of%20Chicago%20goes%20further%2C%20forbidding%20landlords%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chicago.gov%2Fcity%2Fen%2Fdepts%2Fdoh%2Fprovdrs%2Flandlords%2Fsvcs%2Fresidential-landlord-and-tenant-ordinance.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethreatening%20a%20tenant%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20removal%2C%20attempting%20to%20keep%20a%20tenant%20from%20their%20home%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bincapacitating%26quot%3B%20appliances%20unless%20it%20is%20to%20fix%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202006%20bill%20that%20would%20have%20defined%20illegal%20lockouts%20for%20all%20Illinois%20residents%20was%20defeated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%2039%20states%20where%20lockouts%20are%20only%20a%20civil%20infraction%2C%20landlords%20could%20be%20subject%20to%20fines%20and%20locked-out%20tenants%20may%20sue%20to%20recoup%20their%20losses.%20Texas%20has%20a%20uniquely%20complex%20statute%20on%20the%20books%20that%20prohibits%20lockouts%20only%20under%20very%20particular%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20Texas%20statute%20allows%20some%20landlords%20to%20lawfully%20change%20the%20locks%20or%20withhold%20electricity%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20as%20long%20as%20they%20have%20a%20signed%20lease%20that%20outlines%20this%20power%20and%20the%20tenants%20are%20behind%20on%20their%20rent.%20But%20landlords%20can't%20cut%20off%20a%20tenant's%20electricity%20if%20the%20National%20Weather%20Service%20projects%20a%20high%20temperature%20of%20less%20than%2032%20Fahrenheit.%20And%20it's%20too%20hot%20to%20cut%20off%20electricity%20if%20there%20has%20been%20a%20heat%20advisory%20within%20the%20past%20two%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20also%20states%20tenants%20can%20contest%20an%20electricity%20shutoff%20with%20a%20note%20from%20a%20health%20provider%20saying%20someone%20will%20suffer%20serious%20illness%20because%20of%20it%2C%20but%20that%20note%20is%20only%20good%20for%20up%20to%2063%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20legal%20lockout%2C%20Texas%20landlords%20must%20provide%20the%20new%20key%20upon%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20all%20the%20landlords%20who%20do%20it%2C%20do%20it%20correctly%2C%26quot%3B%20Fred%20Fuchs%2C%20an%20attorney%20with%20Texas%20RioGrande%20Legal%20Aid%2C%20said%20of%20the%20law.%20%26quot%3BThat%20other%20states%20don't%20allow%20this%20or%20that%20doesn't%20get%20you%20very%20far%20in%20Texas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECalls%20for%20greater%20enforcement%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20depths%20of%20COVID%2C%20there%20was%20a%20brief%20moment%20of%20consensus%20among%20federal%20officials%20on%20the%20importance%20of%20housing%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202021%2C%20Democratic%20Rep.%20Steve%20Cohen%20introduced%20a%20bill%20in%20the%20House%20that%20would%20have%20standardized%20the%20need%20to%20go%20to%20court%20for%20an%20eviction%20nationwide%20during%20a%20national%20emergency%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20set%20civil%20penalties%20if%20landlords%20did%20not%20comply.%20The%20act%20reflected%20a%20pandemic-era%20recognition%20of%20how%20important%20it%20was%20to%20public%20health%20to%20keep%20people%20housed.%20But%20it%20stalled%20in%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20later%2C%20an%20effort%20led%20by%20Senate%20Democrat%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2Fbill%2F117th-congress%2Fsenate-bill%2F2182%2Fall-actions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMichael%20Bennet%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20fund%20data%20collection%20on%20lockouts%20similarly%20stalled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20the%20face%20of%20congressional%20inaction%2C%20Sarah%20Saadian%2C%20a%20policy%20expert%20with%20the%20National%20Low%20Income%20Housing%20Coalition%2C%20says%20there's%20room%20for%20federal%20regulators%20to%20step%20in.%20Both%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%20and%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%2C%20she%20said%2C%20have%20a%20mandate%20to%20monitor%20abusive%20consumer%20practices%20and%20could%20%26quot%3Bfocus%20more%20explicitly%20on%20renters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%20a%20White%20House%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2FWhite-House-Blueprint-for-a-Renters-Bill-of-Rights.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBlueprint%20for%20a%20Renters'%20Bill%20of%20Rights%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20in%20January%202023%20notes%20that%20the%20FTC%20was%20exploring%20ways%20to%20expand%20its%20authority%20and%20%26quot%3Btake%20action%20against%20acts%20and%20practices%20that%20unfairly%20prevent%20consumers%20from%20obtaining%20and%20retaining%20housing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDouglas%20Farrar%2C%20the%20director%20of%20public%20affairs%20at%20the%20FTC%2C%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20any%20new%20enforcement%20measures.%20The%20CFPB%20also%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelly%2C%20Minnesota's%20assistant%20attorney%20general%2C%20said%20state%20AGs%20could%20step%20up%20in%20enforcing%20tenant%20laws.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20state%20has%20the%20authority%20to%20protect%20consumers%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFuchs%20from%20the%20legal%20clinic%20in%20Texas%20suggested%20that%20better%20police%20training%20could%20make%20a%20difference%20%E2%80%94%20as%20could%20solutions%20that%20don't%20depend%20on%20the%20police%20at%20all.%20Other%20states%20could%20learn%20from%20the%20model%20in%20Texas%2C%20he%20said%2C%20where%20locked-out%20tenants%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flandlord-illegal-lockout-court-tenant-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efile%20a%20complaint%20with%20a%20local%20justice%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20quickly%20regain%20access%20to%20their%20home.%20Other%20tenant%20advocates%20said%20guaranteeing%20the%20right%20to%20counsel%20would%20help%20tenants%20assert%20their%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeymann%2C%20the%20Chicago%20community%20organizer%2C%20said%20she'd%20like%20to%20see%20education%20and%20oversight%20efforts%20targeting%20private%20landlords%20as%20well%20as%20an%20increased%20investment%20in%20public%20housing.%20She%20suggested%20landlords%20who've%20been%20found%20to%20have%20locked%20people%20out%20should%20face%20mandatory%20classes%2C%20or%20sanctions%20if%20they're%20repeat%20offenders%20%E2%80%94%20including%20barring%20them%20from%20renting%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHousing%20should%20not%20be%20dependent%20on%20some%20random%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwho%20gets%20no%20training%20whatsoever.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECredits%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReporting%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECecilia%20Reyes%2C%20Rosemarie%20Ho%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEditing%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEsther%20Kaplan%2C%20Hannah%20Beckler%2C%20John%20Cook%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECopy%20Editing%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EKevin%20Kaplan%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EResearch%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ENarimes%20Parakul%2C%20Darren%20Ankrom%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDesign%20and%20Visuals%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ERebecca%20Zisser%2C%20Isabel%20Fernandez-Pujol%2C%20Randy%20Yeip%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EData%20Visualization%20and%20Audio%20Design%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAnnie%20Fu%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIllustration%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAndrei%20Cojocaru%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPhotography%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBridget%20Bennett%2C%20Callaghan%20O'Hare%2C%20Alyssa%20Pointer%2C%20Abel%20Uribe%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVideo%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETeresa%20Zhang%2C%20Robert%20Leslie%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftbimedia.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com%2Fbistudios%2F_00%2Fdev_edit%2Fgraphics%2F2024%2F04%2F2024-04-evictions-header%2Findex.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20data-chart%3D%5C%22scrolly%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fillegal-wrongful-evictions-law-enforcement-police-court-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720606382000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666211fecc442a2f676ecdd0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fillegal-wrongful-evictions-law-enforcement-police-court-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tenants%20facing%20illegal%20evictions%20often%20call%20police%20for%20help%20but%20spotty%20laws%2C%20training%2C%20and%20enforcement%20mean%20landlords%20rarely%20face%20penalties.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22creyes%40insider.com%20(Cecilia%20Reyes)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fillegal-wrongful-evictions-law-enforcement-police-court-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20renters%20get%20locked%20out%2C%20it's%20unlikely%20they'll%20ever%20get%20back%20in.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20couple%20standing%20in%20front%20of%20the%20car%20they%20live%20in.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c76add1c84a0eaca818d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHenisha%20Dunn%2C%20right%2C%20and%20her%20fianc%C3%A9%20were%20forced%20out%20of%20their%20basement%20apartment%20in%20Atlanta%20in%20February%202023.%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Pointer%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%202022%2C%20a%20young%20aspiring%20permanent%20makeup%20artist%20named%20Henisha%20Dunn%20rented%20a%20basement%20unit%20in%20Atlanta's%20Venetian%20Hills%20neighborhood%20from%20an%20old%20middle-school%20acquaintance%20who%20lived%20on%20the%20home's%20first%20floor.%20The%20damp%2C%20poorly%20lit%20unit%20wasn't%20ideal%20for%20Dunn%20and%20her%20fianc%C3%A9%2C%20but%20the%20couple%20had%20a%20baby%20on%20the%20way%20and%20the%20rent%20was%20much%20cheaper%20than%20anything%20they%20could%20find%20in%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProblems%20quickly%20emerged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20noticed%20leaking%20four%20days%20after%20we%20moved%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Dunn%20said.%20After%20making%20some%20inadequate%20repairs%2C%20she%20said%2C%20their%20landlord%2C%20a%20woman%20named%20Zion%20Griffin%2C%20refused%20to%20do%20any%20more%20work%20and%20instead%20tried%20to%20get%20them%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGriffin%20tried%20everything%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20the%20young%20couple%2C%20repeatedly%20filing%20for%20eviction%20in%20court%20and%20then%20pursuing%20informal%2C%20in%20some%20cases%20illegal%2C%20tactics%20to%20get%20them%20out.%20By%20October%2C%20one%20of%20those%20tactics%20was%20blocking%20the%20couple's%20rent%20payments%2C%20an%20email%20Dunn%20shared%20with%20BI%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGriffin%20then%20hired%20an%20attorney%2C%20who%20wrote%20to%20Dunn%20that%20Griffin%20would%20agree%20to%20forgive%20all%20of%20the%20back%20rent%20for%20%242%2C000%2C%20later%20%241%2C200%2C%20if%20the%20couple%20agreed%20to%20leave.%20If%20they%20didn't%20take%20the%20deal%2C%20the%20attorney%20wrote%2C%20Dunn's%20family%20could%20have%20their%20electricity%20cut%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20in%20everyone's%20best%20interests%20for%20you%20to%20agree%20to%20move%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20attorney%20wrote%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20power%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bdisconnected%20for%20non-payment%26quot%3B%20if%20Griffin%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20obtain%20the%20funds%20to%20pay%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20afternoon%20in%20February%202023%2C%20Dunn%20and%20her%20fianc%C3%A9%20were%20watching%20TV%20while%20their%20infant%20daughter%20took%20a%20nap.%20She%20heard%20the%20sound%20of%20a%20circuit%20break%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Bvoom%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20then%20silence.%20Everything%20went%20dark.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20the%20hell%20was%20that%3F%26quot%3B%20Dunn%20remembers%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20stands%20in%20front%20of%20the%20woods%20by%20herself.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c7d8e40cf2af6e4f609ea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDunn%20was%20a%20young%20mother%20and%20aspiring%20makeup%20artist%20when%20a%20lockout%20left%20her%20homeless.%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Pointer%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20illegal%20pressure%20tactic%20worked.%20As%20their%20groceries%20spoiled%20in%20the%20refrigerator%2C%20Dunn%20said%2C%20the%20young%20family%20stayed%20first%20with%20relatives%2C%20then%20in%20a%20hotel%2C%20returning%20to%20their%20rental%20only%20to%20care%20for%20their%20dog%2C%20Poppa.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Griffin%20filed%20a%20third%20eviction%20in%20April%202023%2C%20court%20records%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(Reached%20by%20phone%2C%20Griffin%20denied%20breaking%20the%20law%20in%20seeking%20to%20evict%20Dunn%20and%20her%20family%2C%20saying%20they%20had%20not%20paid%20for%20their%20portion%20of%20the%20electrical%20bill.%20She%20did%20not%20answer%20a%20follow-up%20email%20with%20detailed%20questions.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvictions%20require%20a%20judge's%20sign-off%20in%20most%20states%2C%20including%20Georgia.%20Strong-arm%20tactics%20like%20cutting%20off%20power%20or%20changing%20the%20locks%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20a%20tenant%20are%20against%20the%20law%20in%20almost%20every%20state.%20Even%20so%2C%20few%20states%20offer%20tenants%20easy%20remedies%20for%20reversing%20an%20illegal%20ouster%2C%20a%20Business%20Insider%20investigation%20has%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20most%20states%2C%20locked-out%20tenants%20have%20no%20recourse%20but%20to%20sue%20their%20landlord%20over%20an%20illegal%20removal%2C%20if%20they%20hope%20to%20recover%20the%20costs%20of%20losing%20all%20their%20possessions%20and%20abruptly%20becoming%20homeless.%20So%20after%20the%20shutoff%2C%20Dunn%20set%20out%20to%20try%20to%20find%20a%20lawyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20she%20didn't%20know%20is%20that%20even%20a%20win%20in%20court%20might%20not%20mean%20she%20could%20get%20back%20into%20her%20home%20%E2%80%94%20or%20reach%20a%20settlement%20large%20enough%20to%20help%20her%20find%20a%20new%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20couple%20holding%20hands%20in%20front%20of%20a%20car.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c7c7950b021b5cae9c2ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDunn%20and%20her%20fianc%C3%A9.%20Their%20landlord%20tried%20everything%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20them%2C%20repeatedly%20filing%20for%20eviction%20in%20court%20and%20then%20pursuing%20illegal%20tactics.%20They're%20still%20looking%20for%20stable%20housing.%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Pointer%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'What's%20the%20worst%20I'm%20going%20to%20owe%3F'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20pored%20over%20state%20laws%20regarding%20evictions%2C%20and%20found%20that%2045%20states%20have%20statutes%20that%20bar%20landlords%20from%20locking%20tenants%20out%20without%20first%20going%20before%20a%20judge.%20Five%20states%2C%20such%20as%20New%20Jersey%20and%20Minnesota%2C%20explicitly%20make%20lockouts%20a%20crime%20punishable%20by%20fines%20or%20jail%20time%3B%20California%20has%20an%20attorney%20general%20directive%20that%20accomplishes%20the%20same%20thing.%20A%20handful%20of%20states%2C%20including%20Texas%20and%20Nevada%2C%20have%20set%20up%20dedicated%20systems%20designed%20to%20restore%20tenants%20to%20their%20homes%20after%20an%20illegal%20lockout.%20In%20most%20states%2C%20however%2C%20lockouts%20are%20only%20a%20civil%20violation%2C%20enforced%20by%20fines%20or%20the%20prospect%20of%20paying%20a%20court%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20for%20most%20tenants%20across%20the%20country%2C%20like%20Dunn%2C%20their%20only%20official%20recourse%20is%20to%20sue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F7GZB4%2F3%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Locked%20out%3F%20What%20you%20can%20do%20varies%20widely%20by%20state.%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22573%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hurdles%20are%20extensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20the%202021%20American%20Housing%20Survey%20indicates%20that%20many%20renters%20would%20struggle%20to%20pay%20for%20an%20attorney.%20While%20homeowners%20had%20an%20average%20household%20income%20of%20%2478%2C000%2C%20renters%20had%20an%20average%20household%20income%20of%20nearly%20half%20that%20%E2%80%94%20%2441%2C000.%20Few%20attorneys%20will%20take%20cases%20on%20contingency%2C%20tenant%20advocates%20said%20%E2%80%94%20an%20agreement%20in%20which%20attorneys%20get%20paid%20only%20if%20they%20win%20a%20case%20%E2%80%94%20as%20many%20states%20don't%20guarantee%20that%20lawyers%20can%20recoup%20fees%20in%20illegal-eviction%20cases.%20And%20data%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20shows%20that%20fewer%20than%20half%20of%20those%20who%20seek%20pro%20bono%20representation%20for%20civil%20suits%20through%20legal%20aid%20organizations%20receive%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20barrier%20to%20even%20get%20to%20court%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Caryn%20Schreiber%2C%20a%20housing%20attorney%20who%20has%20represented%20tenants%20in%20New%20Jersey%20and%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20more%20from%20our%20series%20on%20illegal%20evictions%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fillegal-wrongful-evictions-law-enforcement-police-court-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELocked%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finformal-rental-agreement-affordable-housing-illegal-lockout-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnprotected%20at%20the%20margins%20of%20the%20rental%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDamages%20in%20lockout%20cases%20are%20often%20small%20%E2%80%94%20capped%20by%20state%20law%20in%20proportion%20to%20the%20cost%20of%20lost%20possessions%20or%20temporary%20stays%2C%20or%20capped%20at%20two%20or%20three%20months'%20rent.%20Tenants'%20damaged%20or%20stolen%20possessions%20may%20not%20be%20worth%20a%20large%20amount%20of%20money%2C%20and%20the%20lost%20wages%20for%20days%20of%20missed%20work%20caused%20by%20a%20lockout%20may%20not%20be%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20landlords%20who%20are%20doing%20this%20intentionally%20are%20doing%20a%20cost-benefit%20analysis%2C%26quot%3B%20Paul%20Panusky%2C%20an%20Atlanta%20attorney%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthinking%20to%20themselves%2C%20what's%20the%20worst%20I'm%20going%20to%20owe%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPanusky%20has%20represented%20dozens%20of%20tenants%20in%20wrongful-eviction%20suits.%20His%20most%20successful%20cases%2C%20he%20said%2C%20have%20involved%20six-figure%20settlements%2C%20a%20large%20enough%20penalty%20to%20offer%20real%20deterrence%20for%20a%20landlord.%20He's%20been%20able%20to%20recoup%20those%20amounts%20in%20part%20because%20landlord-tenant%20laws%20in%20Georgia%2C%20which%20don't%20explicitly%20ban%20lockouts%2C%20also%20don't%20set%20specific%20limits%20for%20damages%20related%20to%20an%20improper%20eviction.%20Other%20states%20explicitly%20ban%20lockouts%2C%20but%20cap%20damages%20at%20very%20small%20amounts%3A%20In%20Nevada%2C%20tenants%20are%20awarded%20actual%20damages%2C%20plus%20up%20to%20%242%2C500.%20Michigan%20sets%20it%20as%20three%20times%20actual%20damages%20or%20%24200%2C%20whichever%20is%20greater.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeffrey%20Uno%2C%20the%20managing%20attorney%20for%20the%20eviction%20defense%20center%20at%20the%20Legal%20Aid%20Foundation%20of%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20said%20that%20he%20counsels%20locked-out%20tenants%20that%20lawsuits%20can%20be%20lengthy%20and%20costly%20and%20may%20not%20solve%20the%20immediate%20problem%20of%20a%20place%20to%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhere%20are%20people%20going%20to%20cook%2C%20sleep%2C%20to%20take%20their%20medicine%3F%26quot%3B%20Uno%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20happens%20to%20your%20memorabilia%2C%20your%20old%20pictures%3F%20Those%20things%20matter.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Brogan%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20New%20Jersey%20Apartment%20Association%2C%20a%20group%20representing%20landlords%2C%20property%20managers%2C%20and%20developers%2C%20said%20his%20members%20would%20not%20engage%20in%20illegal%20lockouts%20because%20of%20the%20state's%20protective%20tenant%20laws.%20%26quot%3BTo%20be%20a%20landlord%20in%20New%20Jersey%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI'd%20recommend%20you%20fully%20understand%20the%20law%2C%20because%20it's%20at%20your%20own%20peril%20if%20you%20don't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22940%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20court%20order%20from%20the%20State%20Court%20of%20Fulton%20County%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667d7bd740cf2af6e4f634a6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22826%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhen%20Dunn%20went%20to%20court%20about%20her%20landlord%20shutting%20off%20her%20electricity%2C%20the%20damages%20she%20won%20didn't%20even%20cover%20the%20amount%20of%20back%20rent%20the%20judge%20said%20was%20due.%3Cp%3EState%20Court%20of%20Fulton%20County%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Dunn%2C%20the%20electricity%20shutoff%20was%20a%20turning%20point.%20She%20tried%20to%20find%20a%20lawyer%20but%20couldn't%20afford%20the%20fee.%20An%20Atlanta%20Legal%20Aid%20attorney%20offered%20Dunn%20some%20guidance%2C%20but%20she%20said%20the%20organization%20was%20overwhelmed%20with%20cases%20and%20couldn't%20take%20hers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Griffin's%20third%20eviction%20attempt%20was%20granted%2C%20court%20records%20show.%20Still%20without%20a%20lawyer%2C%20in%20disbelief%20the%20judge%20had%20awarded%20her%20nothing%2C%20Dunn%20filed%20an%20appeal%2C%20again%20bringing%20up%20the%20unrepaired%20water%20leaks%20and%20electricity%20cutoff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20time%2C%20the%20court%20found%20the%20utility%20shutoff%20was%20tantamount%20to%20an%20illegal%20eviction.%20A%20judge%20awarded%20her%20%24250%20for%20it%20and%20%241%2C000%20for%20the%20landlord's%20lack%20of%20repairs.%20But%20her%20eviction%20was%20still%20granted.%20What%20the%20couple%20received%20didn't%20even%20cover%20the%20amount%20of%20rent%20the%20court%20said%20Griffin%20was%20due.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ordeal%20was%20draining%2C%20Dunn%20said%2C%20especially%20with%20a%20new%20baby%20in%20tow.%20She%20and%20her%20family%20still%20don't%20have%20a%20new%20apartment%2C%20she%20said%2C%20and%20the%20eviction%20cases%20on%20her%20record%20don't%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20the%20judicial%20system%20failed%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFew%20tickets%2C%20fewer%20fines%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20cities%20offer%20more%20significant%20protections%20than%20state%20laws%20require.%20BI%20looked%20at%20how%20eight%20major%20cities%20with%20a%20high%20density%20of%20renters%20handle%20illegal%20lockouts%20and%20found%20only%20one%2C%20Chicago%2C%20that%20uses%20municipal%20fines%20as%20a%20way%20to%20discourage%20landlords%20from%20breaking%20these%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%2C%20where%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20city's%20residents%20are%20renters%2C%20a%20residential%20lockout%20is%20a%20municipal%20violation%20and%20the%20police%20can%20issue%20tickets%2C%20similar%20to%20a%20traffic%20infraction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20citations%20are%20processed%20by%20the%20city's%20administrative%20hearings%20department.%20If%20sustained%2C%20they%20result%20in%20a%20fine%20paid%20out%20to%20the%20city%2C%20commonly%20about%20%24500.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20such%20outcomes%20are%20rare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20reviewed%20two%20years'%20worth%20of%20lockout%20cases%20from%20the%20department%20and%20found%20city%20lawyers%20routinely%20dismissed%20tickets%2C%20often%20without%20documenting%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20citations%20were%20dismissed%20because%20of%20paperwork%20errors.%20Others%20were%20thrown%20out%20because%20the%20tenant%20did%20not%20attend%20the%20hearing%2C%20a%20common%20occurrence.%20Administrative%20law%20judges%20%E2%80%94%20lawyers%20contracted%20by%20the%20city%20to%20rule%20on%20the%20cases%20%E2%80%94%20often%20spent%20less%20than%20two%20minutes%20on%20each%20ticket%20and%20sometimes%20appeared%20unfamiliar%20with%20relevant%20city%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecords%20show%20most%20final%20hearings%20are%20held%20more%20than%20a%20month%20after%20a%20lockout%20occurs%2C%20long%20after%20the%20tenants%20would%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20find%20a%20new%20place%20to%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20part%20of%20the%20fine%20ever%20goes%20to%20the%20tenants.%20And%20the%20judges%20don't%20have%20the%20power%20to%20order%20a%20tenant%20restored%20to%20their%20home.%20For%20damages%2C%20as%20in%20other%20locales%2C%20the%20tenant%20has%20to%20sue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F4eEWG%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Landlords%20are%20rarely%20penalized%20for%20illegal%20lockouts%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22827%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20first%20day%20they%20began%20tracking%20the%20phenomenon%20in%20February%202021%20through%20March%202023%2C%20the%20Chicago%20police%20received%20more%20than%203%2C000%20calls%20complaining%20of%20illegal%20lockouts.%20Police%20officers%20ticketed%20only%2079%20landlords%20over%20that%20time%20period%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20Chicago's%20hearing%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20half%20of%20those%20tickets%20were%20thrown%20out.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20landlords%20were%20found%20guilty%20of%20locking%20out%20their%20tenants%20seven%20times%20over%20those%20two%20years.%20Fifteen%20other%20landlords%20were%20fined%20after%20failing%20to%20appear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20in%20Chicago%20only%20about%20one%20in%20every%20140%20lockout%20calls%20results%20in%20a%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%20last%20year%2C%20for%20example%2C%20a%20police%20officer%20ticketed%20a%20landlord%20for%20switching%20the%20locks%20to%20the%20front%20door%20in%20his%20six-unit%20building.%20Four%20months%20later%2C%20the%20owner%20attended%20a%20hearing%20where%20the%20citation%20was%20thrown%20out%20at%20the%20request%20of%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChicago's%20hearings%20department%20did%20not%20provide%20documentation%20of%20why%20city%20lawyers%20dropped%20the%20case%2C%20and%20the%20administrative%20judge%20didn't%20ask%2C%20according%20to%20audio%20of%20the%20hearing.%20Instead%2C%20he%20issued%20a%20weak%20warning%20to%20the%20landlord%20to%20follow%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20you%20like%20to%20do%20certain%20things%2C%20but%20you%20just%20stick%20to%20the%20landlord-tenant%20ordinance%2C%20OK%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20office%20of%20Chicago's%20mayor%2C%20Brandon%20Johnson%2C%20which%20oversees%20both%20the%20hearings%20department%20and%20the%20city%20attorneys%20who%20appear%20there%2C%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Inside%20the%20Chicago's%20Central%20Hearing%20Facility.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668434031aace5b3ada3ba78%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222338%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELockout%20hearings%20are%20held%20at%20Chicago's%20Central%20Hearing%20Facility.%3Cp%3EAbel%20Uribe%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20of%20one%20landlord%2C%20Rolando%20Quebrado%2C%20illustrates%20how%20ineffective%20the%20tickets%20are%20in%20deterring%20landlord%20lockouts.%20Quebrado%20was%20cited%20at%20least%20twice%20in%202021%20over%20illegal%20evictions%20in%20Chicago's%20Jefferson%20Park%20neighborhood.%20The%20first%20time%2C%20a%20police%20officer%20wrote%20a%20ticket%20for%20illegally%20changing%20locks.%20About%20three%20weeks%20later%2C%20an%20officer%20wrote%20another%20ticket%20because%20Quebrado%20turned%20off%20the%20electricity%20at%20the%20same%20duplex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20administrative%20judge%20dismissed%20both%20citations%20because%20the%20officers%20did%20not%20write%20the%20date%20of%20the%20hearing%20clearly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20second%20citation%20in%20a%20row%20for%20the%20same%20person%20where%20the%20only%20scribble%2C%20the%20only%20problem%2C%20the%20only%20illegible%20section%20is%20the%20date%20of%20the%20hearing%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20administrative%20judge%20said.%20%26quot%3BEither%20they%20deliberately%20are%20trying%20to%20make%20certain%20that%20the%20respondent%20shows%20up%20on%20the%20wrong%20date%20...%20or%20they're%20deliberately%20giving%20the%20respondent%20an%20out%20of%20being%20found%20not%20liable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQuebrado%20said%20the%20tickets%20were%20a%20big%20misunderstanding.%20He%20said%20he%20had%20recently%20purchased%20the%20home%2C%20not%20intending%20to%20become%20a%20landlord%20to%20the%20family%20living%20in%20the%20basement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20he%20changed%20the%20locks%20only%20because%20he%20didn't%20know%20which%20keys%20corresponded%20to%20which%20door%2C%20and%20that%20the%20basement%20electricity%20was%20cut%20off%20by%20accident%20when%20he%20registered%20meters%20for%20the%20home's%20other%20floors%20with%20the%20electric%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20should%20have%20done%20more%20research%2C%26quot%3B%20Quebrado%20said.%20But%20he%20said%20he%20had%20a%20young%20family%20of%20his%20own%20and%20felt%20overwhelmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20was%20me%20not%20being%20knowledgeable%20about%20being%20a%20landlord%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChicago%20has%20also%20repeatedly%20cited%20big%20landlords.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20Pangea%2C%20which%20is%20embroiled%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcookcountyrecord.com%2Fstories%2F628997588-class-action-pangea-allegedly-misleads-tenants-into-leasing-problem-apartments-ignores-complaints-threatens-objectors%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20class-action%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhsplegal.com%2Fhsprd-wins-important-victory-in-class-action-lawsuit-against-pangea-properties%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunsafe%20conditions%20and%20disrepair%20at%20hundreds%20of%20properties%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20city%2C%20was%20ticketed%20for%20locking%20out%20tenants%20at%20least%20three%20times%20in%20recent%20years.%20(Pangea%20has%20denied%20the%20claims%20in%20the%20suit%20and%20declined%20to%20comment%20to%20BI%20on%20legal%20matters.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Troy%20Marr%2C%20the%20words%20an%20officer%20chose%20when%20issuing%20his%20landlord%20a%20ticket%20became%20a%20sticking%20point%20at%20his%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarr's%20access%20to%20his%20building's%20common%20areas%20was%20cut%20off%20through%20an%20app%20in%20November%2C%20leaving%20him%20unable%20to%20get%20into%20the%20lobby%2C%20garage%2C%20or%20elevator.%20He%20had%20a%20physical%20key%20to%20his%2022nd-floor%20apartment%20in%20a%20swanky%20new%20building%20in%20River%20North%2C%20but%20he%20found%20himself%20in%20the%20bizarre%20situation%20of%20having%20to%20follow%20other%20tenants%20inside%20or%20wait%20for%20the%20concierge%20to%20escort%20him%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20called%20the%20Chicago%20police%20multiple%20times%2C%20Marr%20said.%20An%20officer%20issued%20a%20ticket%20to%20the%20building's%20management%20company%2C%20then%20Common%20Living%2C%20but%20only%20after%20he%20took%20a%20trip%20to%20his%20local%20precinct%20and%20talked%20to%20a%20sergeant%2C%20Marr%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Troy%20Marr%20standing%20in%20front%20of%20a%20glass-windowed%20skyscraper%20that%20has%20the%20name%20The%20808%20on%20the%20side.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c77e750b021b5cae9c0df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETroy%20Marr%20rented%20a%2022nd-floor%20apartment%20in%20a%20new%20building%20near%20downtown%20Chicago.%20There%2C%20according%20to%20a%20police%20ticket%2C%20he%20got%20locked%20out%20of%20the%20building%20by%20means%20of%20an%20app.%3Cp%3EAbel%20Uribe%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBuilding%20access%20was%20terminated%20without%20court%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20officer%20wrote%2C%20telling%20Common%20Living's%20James%20Byczek%20to%20restore%20Marr's%20access.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EByczek%20told%20the%20administrative%20judge%20at%20the%20hearing%20that%20there%20had%20been%20no%20lockout%2C%20a%20claim%20he%20repeated%20to%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20is%20it%20a%20lockout%20if%20he%20is%20in%20and%20out%20of%20his%20unit%3F%26quot%3B%20Byczek%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20briefly%20questioning%20whether%20he%20had%20jurisdictional%20standing%2C%20the%20administrative%20law%20judge%2C%20Michael%20Dudek%2C%20sided%20with%20Common%20Living.%20He%20wasn't%20convinced%20Marr%20had%20been%20locked%20out%20for%20several%20days%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20the%20lone%20police%20ticket%20didn't%20mention%20the%20chronic%20access%20problems%20that%20had%20preceded%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaybe%20it's%20a%20little%20inconvenient%2C%26quot%3B%20Dudek%20said%20of%20Marr's%20tortured%20access%20to%20his%20unit.%20%26quot%3BDid%20he%20get%20kicked%20out%3F%20No%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarr%20was%20flabbergasted%20by%20the%20result.%20(He%20separately%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20his%20landlord%20over%20the%20lockout%2C%20which%20remains%20pending.%20According%20to%20the%20building's%20website%2C%20Common%20Living%20no%20longer%20manages%20the%20property.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20deterring%20landlords%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20Chicago's%20ticketing%20process.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20a%20tenant.%20They're%20a%20landlord.%20I%20can't%20get%20to%20my%20unit%20now.%20Black%20and%20white%2C%20that's%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22James%20Byczek%20stands%20outside%20the%20City%20of%20Chicago%20Central%20Hearing%20Facility.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c78aa40cf2af6e4f6082d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222390%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJames%20Byczek%2C%20of%20Common%20Living%2C%20a%20management%20company%20that%20ran%20the%20building%20where%20Marr%20lives%2C%20appears%20for%20a%20hearing%20about%20Marr's%20lockout%20complaint.%20It%20was%20thrown%20out.%3Cp%3EAbel%20Uribe%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20quick%20relief%20option%20in%20Nevada%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20visited%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20where%20tenants%20have%20a%20pathway%20to%20fight%20lockouts%20that's%20not%20dependent%20on%20the%20police.%20The%20state%20of%20Nevada%20has%20a%20system%20of%20justice%20courts%20in%20which%20a%20tenant%20can%20file%20a%20petition%20for%20%26quot%3Bexpedited%20relief%26quot%3B%20after%20an%20illegal%20lockout%20or%20utility%20disconnection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20system%20is%20designed%20to%20offer%20quick%20results.%20But%20tenants%20have%20to%20move%20fast%2C%20too.%20By%20statute%2C%20they%20have%20at%20most%20eight%20working%20days%20to%20file%20a%20complaint%20and%20get%20an%20independent%20third%20party%20to%20serve%20notice%20to%20their%20landlord.%20In%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20tenants%20need%20to%20have%20an%20email%20address%20to%20make%20an%20electronic%20filing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20fall%2C%20Hearing%20Master%20David%20Brown%20presided%20over%20hearings%20BI%20attended%20virtually%20and%20in%20person%20at%20Las%20Vegas'%20Regional%20Justice%20Center.%20The%20sounds%20of%20fidgeting%20children%2C%20crying%20babies%2C%20and%20the%20occasional%20snore%20would%20sometimes%20rise%20above%20hushed%20chatter.%20During%20one%20early-November%20court%20session%2C%20locked-out%20tenants%20who%20filed%20for%20expedited%20relief%20waited%20for%20nearly%20an%20hour%20for%20their%20cases%20to%20get%20called%3A%20Landlords'%20formal%20eviction%20cases%20were%20heard%20in%20the%20same%20courtroom%20and%20got%20called%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20front%20of%20the%20judge%2C%20two%20long%20tables%20with%20placards%20reading%20%26quot%3Btenant%2Fdefendant%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Blandlord%2Fplaintiff%26quot%3B%20hinted%20at%20how%20the%20courts%20are%20dominated%20by%20landlords%20seeking%20evictions%20%E2%80%94%20rather%20than%20tenants%20seeking%20redress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Someone%20walking%20up%20the%20steps%20outside%20the%20Regional%20Justice%20Center%20in%20Nevada.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c7a8740cf2af6e4f608d7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAt%20Nevada's%20justice%20courts%2C%20like%20this%20one%20in%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20tenants%20have%20an%20unusual%20pathway%3A%20They%20can%20petition%20to%20regain%20access%20to%20their%20apartments%20after%20a%20lockout.%3Cp%3EBridget%20Bennett%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20afternoon%2C%20Brown%20had%20three%20cases%20on%20his%20docket%20in%20which%20tenants%20were%20alleging%20they'd%20been%20illegally%20locked%20out%20and%20dozens%20of%20cases%20in%20which%20landlords%20were%20seeking%20formal%20evictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20two%20hours%20in%2C%20Brown%20started%20calling%20the%20lockout%20complaints.%20Brown%20denied%20one%20because%20the%20tenant%20hadn't%20properly%20served%20her%20landlord%2C%20which%20he%20said%20violated%20the%20landlord's%20due-process%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20woman%20offered%20up%20that%20she%20had%20been%20in%20the%20hospital%20and%20her%20home%20was%20infested%20with%20mold.%20Brown%20cut%20her%20off%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMa'am%2C%20you're%20starting%20to%20testify%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BToday%20I%20only%20can%20proceed%20if%20there%20is%20a%20hearing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20case%20met%20the%20same%20fate.%20That%20tenant%2C%20also%20a%20woman%2C%20said%20she%20had%20asked%20the%20constable%20to%20serve%20her%20landlord%20but%20had%20been%20turned%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrown%20countered%20that%20she%20should%20have%20found%20another%20way%20to%20serve%20her%20landlord.%20The%20woman%20was%20desperate%20and%20tried%20to%20plead%20her%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20texts%20of%20them%20saying%20they'll%20throw%20my%20stuff%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Brown%20simply%20directed%20her%20to%20the%20courthouse's%20self-help%20legal%20center%2C%20a%20sort%20of%20help%20desk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20woman%20was%20in%20tears%20afterward%20and%20told%20BI%20she%20would%20likely%20sleep%20on%20the%20streets%20that%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20hard%20statute%20because%20of%20the%20timing%2C%26quot%3B%20Brown%20told%20BI%20after%20the%20hearing.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%20tenants%20don't%20know%20what%20they're%20doing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20judge%20sits%20in%20court%20and%20hands%20paper%20to%20defendant.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c6a4d50b021b5cae9b8a4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHearing%20master%20David%20Brown%20at%20the%20Las%20Vegas%20Regional%20Justice%20Center%20in%20November.%20He%20tossed%20multiple%20cases%20because%20tenants%20failed%20to%20properly%20serve%20notice%20to%20their%20landlords.%3Cp%3EBridget%20Bennett%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20requested%20data%20on%20filings%20for%20relief%20after%20an%20illegal%20eviction%20since%202019%20in%20the%20Las%20Vegas%20Justice%20Court.%20To%20gauge%20how%20often%20tenants%20prevailed%20by%20filing%20lockout%20complaints%2C%20BI%20analyzed%20the%20outcomes%20for%2067%20cases%2C%20a%205%25%20sample.%20Out%20of%20those%2067%20cases%2C%20BI%20identified%2011%20petitions%20where%20relief%20was%20granted%2C%20compared%20with%2056%20that%20were%20denied%20or%20dismissed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20details%20the%20courts%20provided%2C%20the%20most%20common%20reason%20tenant%20complaints%20were%20set%20aside%20was%20tenants%20failing%20to%20file%20on%20time%20or%20improperly%20serving%20their%20landlords.%20Others%20were%20denied%20or%20dismissed%20over%20lack%20of%20sufficient%20proof%2C%20or%20because%20the%20hearing%20master%20judged%20them%20irrelevant%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20a%20flooded%20unit%20that%20didn't%20constitute%20a%20lockout.%20In%20seven%20of%20the%20complaints%20BI%20sampled%2C%20the%20removals%20were%20deemed%20legal%20after%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FaPc8P%2F6%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Nevada%20tenants%20face%20steep%20odds%20in%20reversing%20lockouts%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22624%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20observed%20similar%20patterns%20in%20court.%20One%20woman%20filed%20the%20wrong%20court%20form.%20Another%20gave%20notice%20of%20the%20hearing%20by%20email%2C%20which%20the%20judge%20didn't%20consider%20valid.%20A%20third%20tenant%20was%20unaware%20of%20the%20requirement%20to%20serve%20notice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20tenants%20did%20receive%20help.%20Two%20family%20members%20were%20able%20to%20stay%20in%20their%20home%20and%20won%20a%20%24600%20rent%20reduction%20after%20their%20landlord%20admitted%20to%20locking%20a%20gate%20to%20their%20rental.%20Two%20other%20landlords%20were%20ordered%20to%20let%20their%20tenants%20back%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20anti-lockout%20judgment%20precludes%20a%20landlord%20from%20pursuing%20a%20legal%20eviction%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrown%20heard%20the%20case%20of%20a%20woman%20whose%20landlord%20had%20sent%20a%20maintenance%20worker%20to%20change%20her%20locks%20while%20her%2011-year-old%20daughter%20was%20home%20alone.%20The%20landlord%20had%20started%20the%20eviction%20process%2C%20the%20judge%20noted%2C%20but%20shouldn't%20have%20changed%20the%20locks%20prematurely.%20He%20ruled%20in%20the%20woman's%20favor%20and%20ordered%20the%20landlord%20to%20change%20the%20locks%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20haven't%20been%20removed%2C%20so%20I%20guess%20that's%20the%20good%20news%2C%26quot%3B%20Brown%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20guess%20I'll%20see%20you%20when%20the%20case%20comes%20before%20the%20court.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20modest%20penalties%20appear%20to%20have%20done%20little%20to%20dissuade%20landlords%20from%20locking%20tenants%20out.%20BI's%20analysis%20of%20data%20from%20the%20Las%20Vegas%20Justice%20Court%20found%20at%20least%20100%20landlords%20who%20faced%20multiple%20lockout%20complaints%20from%202019%20through%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20streamlined%20system%20in%20Texas%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20examined%20another%20state%20%E2%80%94%20Texas%20%E2%80%94%20where%20tenants%20can%20file%20an%20emergency%20petition%20to%20reenter%20their%20home%20after%20an%20illegal%20eviction%2C%20in%20this%20case%20by%20getting%20something%20called%20a%20writ%20of%20reentry.%20The%20Texas%20process%20has%20a%20key%20advantage%20for%20tenants%3A%20They're%20not%20burdened%20with%20having%20to%20serve%20their%20landlord%20before%20a%20justice%20of%20the%20peace%20can%20make%20a%20ruling%20on%20their%20case.%20The%20landlord%20doesn't%20even%20have%20to%20be%20present%2C%20though%20they%20can%20later%20contest%20the%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20requested%20data%20from%202019%20through%202023%20on%20such%20filings%20in%20Harris%20County%2C%20where%20Houston%20is%20the%20county%20seat.%20We%20received%20742%20tenant%20petitions%20(some%20of%20them%20filed%20by%20commercial%20tenants)%20and%20analyzed%20the%20outcomes%20as%20of%20March%201.%20Of%20those%2C%20326%20cases%20%E2%80%94%20nearly%20half%20%E2%80%94%20showed%20residential%20tenants%20were%20granted%20an%20order%20to%20get%20back%20into%20their%20home%20or%20their%20landlords%20were%20ordered%20to%20turn%20their%20utilities%20back%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22781%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Writ%20of%20Re-Entry%20from%20the%20Harris%20County%20Justice%20Court%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668c06771aace5b3ada4ff18%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22360%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20Texas%2C%20locked-out%20tenants%20can%20file%20a%20complaint%20with%20a%20Justice%20Court%20and%20win%20a%20Writ%20of%20Re-Entry%20forcing%20their%20landlord%20to%20let%20them%20back%20into%20their%20home.%3Cp%3EHarris%20County%20Justice%20Court%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20orders%20ranged%20from%20judgments%20for%20tenants%20of%20less%20than%20%24200%20%E2%80%94%20to%20cover%20the%20cost%20of%20filing%20and%20serving%20their%20landlords%20%E2%80%94%20to%20same-day%20orders%20to%20let%20tenants%20back%20into%20their%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20case%2C%20constable%20officers%20tried%20on%20more%20than%20one%20day%20to%20contact%20property%20managers%20to%20get%20a%20tenant%20back%20in.%20In%20another%2C%20a%20tenant's%20successful%20petition%20to%20have%20her%20electricity%20turned%20back%20on%20resulted%20in%20fixes%20to%20other%20units%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDana%20Karni%2C%20the%20litigation%20director%20at%20Lone%20Star%20Legal%20Aid%20in%20Houston%2C%20said%20few%20locked%20out%20tenants%20know%20they%20can%20ask%20a%20justice%20court%20for%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20every%20illegal%20lockout%20where%20a%20tenant%20actually%20stands%20on%20his%20or%20her%20rights%2C%20there%20are%20multiple%20lockouts%20where%20a%20tenant%20has%20no%20idea%20they%20have%20rights%2C%26quot%3B%20Karni%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fojo4X%2F7%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Tenant%20filings%20have%20risen%20in%20states%20with%20speedy%20review%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22462%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20there%20is%20little%20evidence%20that%20these%20outcomes%20were%20enough%20to%20deter%20landlords%20from%20future%20lockouts.%20BI%20found%20that%20at%20least%2026%20landlords%20were%20sued%20repeatedly%20over%20claims%20of%20illegal%20lockouts%2C%20a%20likely%20undercount%20given%20that%20landlords%20are%20named%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrooke%20Boyett%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Harris%20County's%20Office%20of%20County%20Administration%2C%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20efficacy%20of%20the%20system%20in%20dissuading%20landlords%20from%20locking%20out%20tenants%2C%20referring%20BI%20to%20the%20court%2C%20but%20noted%20that%20the%20county%20has%20put%20%249%20million%20in%20COVID%20recovery%20funds%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.click2houston.com%2Fnews%2Flocal%2F2024%2F03%2F01%2F2-harris-county-commissioners-to-highlight-new-funding-for-eviction-legal-aid%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520response%252C%2520Harris%2520County%2520leaders%2Caid%2520to%2520renters%2520facing%2520eviction.%26amp%3Btext%3DBoth%2520organizations%2520had%2520a%2520target%2Cserving%2520more%2520than%25207%252C200%2520individuals%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etoward%20eviction%20defense%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20county's%20court%20management%20office%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20with%20Nevada%2C%20a%20Texas%20landlord%20can%20file%20for%20a%20lawful%20eviction%20at%20any%20time%2C%20even%20after%20a%20justice%20court%20determines%20they%20illegally%20locked%20out%20their%20tenant.%20An%20eviction%20order%20overrides%20one%20to%20restore%20a%20locked-out%20tenant%20to%20their%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22762%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20plaintiff's%20complaint%20from%20the%20Harris%20County%20Justice%20Court%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668c06b0098114dafd1a4c78%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22442%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOne%20Houston%20man%20was%20living%20with%20his%20sister%3B%20when%20he%20decided%20to%20move%2C%20she%20locked%20him%20out%2C%20with%20all%20his%20possessions%20inside.%20He%20complained%20and%20was%20granted%20a%20Writ%20of%20Re-Entry.%3Cp%3EHarris%20County%20Justice%20Court%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMarlon%20Coleman%20thought%20filing%20a%20complaint%20would%20be%20his%20ticket%20back%20into%20his%20apartment.%20But%20he%20was%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColeman%20said%20his%20property%20manager%2C%20Texas%20Excel%20Property%20Management%2C%20cut%20his%20electricity%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20Houston%20summer.%20With%20temperatures%20climbing%20to%20100%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%2C%20Coleman%20left%20his%20place%20in%20the%20Greater%20Inwood%20neighborhood%20to%20stay%20with%20family.%20When%20he%20returned%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20later%2C%20in%20the%20evening%2C%20his%20apartment%20locks%20were%20changed%2C%20he%20said%2C%20and%20there%20was%20a%20note%20from%20property%20management%20saying%20they%20would%20consider%20the%20unit%20abandoned.%20Coleman's%20bed%2C%20his%20TV%2C%20and%20most%20of%20his%20clothes%2C%20he%20said%2C%20were%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColeman%20called%20911.%20But%20when%20the%20police%20arrived%2C%20he%20said%2C%20they%20didn't%20even%20get%20out%20of%20their%20squad%20car%2C%20saying%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fillegal-wrongful-evictions-law-enforcement-police-court-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethere%20was%20nothing%20they%20could%20do%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Records%20show%20his%20call%20was%20closed%20as%20civil%20the%20same%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShay%20Awosiyan%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Houston%20Police%20Department%2C%20said%20Coleman%20was%20directed%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bbest%20avenue%26quot%3B%20after%20he%20called.%20%26quot%3BMr.%20Coleman%20was%20provided%20the%20phone%20number%20for%20the%20constable's%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20Awosiyan%20said.%20%26quot%3BOur%20officer%20was%20out%20there%2C%20helped%20him%20out%2C%20and%20provided%20information%20to%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColeman%20said%20he%20confronted%20property%20managers%20at%20Excel's%20Villa%20Nueva%20apartments%20the%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20couldn't%20give%20me%20an%20explanation%2C%26quot%3B%20Coleman%20said.%20%26quot%3BTo%20be%20done%20like%20this%2C%20it's%20ridiculous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marlon%20Coleman%20sitting%20on%20a%20step%20outside%20his%20old%20home.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c7993d1c84a0eaca81a36%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMarlon%20Coleman%20said%20his%20property%20manager%20cut%20his%20electricity%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20hot%20Houston%20summer.%20When%20he%20returned%20a%20few%20days%20later%2C%20he'd%20been%20locked%20out.%3Cp%3ECallaghan%20O'Hare%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20filed%20a%20petition%20with%20the%20court%20alleging%20he'd%20been%20illegally%20locked%20out%2C%20asking%20a%20judge%20to%20order%20the%20landlord%20to%20let%20him%20back%20in.%20On%20the%20day%20of%20his%20court%20appearance%2C%20he%20said%2C%20a%20woman%20representing%20the%20landlord%20told%20him%20he'd%20get%20a%20key%20and%20a%20chance%20to%20get%20back%20his%20furniture%20and%20his%20other%20possessions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColeman's%20complaint%20was%20voluntarily%20dismissed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Coleman%20said%20he%20was%20never%20let%20back%20into%20his%20unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%20Excel%2C%20which%20manages%20Villa%20Nueva%20Apartments%2C%20confirmed%20Coleman%20was%20no%20longer%20living%20at%20the%20building%20but%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20additional%20queries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeaving%20the%20burden%20on%20tenants%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESchreiber%2C%20the%20housing%20attorney%2C%20said%20housing%20remedies%20for%20tenants%20are%20fundamentally%20flawed.%20They're%20not%20strong%20enough%20to%20deter%20landlords%20from%20locking%20out%20tenants.%20They%20rarely%20result%20in%20what%20tenants%20most%20want%3A%20getting%20back%20into%20their%20apartments.%20And%20they%20depend%20entirely%20on%20tenants%20taking%20legal%20action%20on%20their%20own%20behalf%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20needs%20to%20be%20a%20shift%20away%20from%20burdening%20tenants%20with%20the%20responsibility%20to%20prove%20they%20are%20entitled%20to%20habitable%20condition%2C%20access%20to%20their%20homes%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSomeone's%20right%20to%20property%20isn't%20greater%20than%20someone's%20right%20to%20a%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20cities%20and%20counties%20have%20sought%20to%20strengthen%20protections%20against%20evictions%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20only%20to%20face%20a%20backlash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Miami-Dade%20County%20passed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.miamidade.gov%2Fgovaction%2Fmatter.asp%3Fmatter%3D221055%26file%3Dfalse%26fileAnalysis%3Dfalse%26yearFolder%3DY2022%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20tenant's%20bill%20of%20rights%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20underlines%20the%20illegality%20of%20lockouts%20and%20limits%20a%20landlord's%20ability%20to%20harass%20tenants.%20It%20also%20bars%20landlords%20from%20requiring%20a%20prospective%20tenant%20to%20disclose%20their%20eviction%20history%20on%20a%20rental%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20March%2C%20a%20Republican%20state%20senator%2C%20Jay%20Trumbull%2C%20introduced%20a%20preemption%20bill%20specifically%20to%20undercut%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20more%20egregious%20local%20ordinances%20happens%20to%20be%20in%20Miami-Dade%20County%2C%26quot%3B%20Trumbull%20said%20on%20the%20Senate%20floor.%20He%20had%20the%20backing%20of%20the%20local%20real-estate%20lobby%2C%20Florida%20Realtors%2C%20who%20have%20said%20local%20laws%20risk%20discouraging%20development%20and%20worsening%20rental%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Governor%20DeSantis%20stands%20in%20front%20of%20a%20crowd.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c7bb450b021b5cae9c28b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGov.%20Ron%20DeSantis%20of%20Florida%20signed%20legislation%20last%20year%20preempting%20local%20laws%20that%20protect%20tenants.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Raedle%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20supported%20both%20of%20those%20bills%20due%20to%20their%20emphasis%20on%20the%20protection%20of%20private%20property%20rights%2C%20which%20is%20a%20priority%20of%20our%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20Tom%20Butler%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Florida%20Realtors%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGov.%20Ron%20DeSantis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnlihc.org%2Fresource%2Fflorida-governor-signs-preemption-legislation-impacting-tenant-protections-across-state%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esigned%20the%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20law%20last%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Houston%2C%20where%20Coleman%20was%20locked%20out%2C%20the%20city%20council%20can't%20easily%20enact%20a%20law%20to%20help%20tenants%20like%20him%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%20lawmakers%20followed%20Florida's%20lead%20in%20dissolving%20municipal%20tenant%20protections%20by%20passing%20a%20far-reaching%20preemption%20law%20that%20nullifies%20local%20regulations%20on%20not%20only%20housing%2C%20but%20also%20labor%2C%20agriculture%2C%20finance%2C%20and%20natural%20resources%2C%20if%20they're%20inconsistent%20with%20state%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill's%20backers%20argued%20that%20it%20simplified%20a%20patchwork%20of%20local%20laws.%20Detractors%20called%20it%20the%20%26quot%3BDeath%20Star%20bill.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDallas%20and%20Austin%20had%20in%20recent%20years%20passed%20protections%20for%20tenants%20that%20included%20the%20right%20to%20remedy%20a%20lease%20violation%20or%20late%20payment%20before%20an%20eviction%20is%20filed.%20A%20last-minute%20amendment%20took%20aim%20at%20them%2C%20explicitly%20barring%20local%20laws%20that%20%26quot%3Bprohibit%2C%20restrict%20or%20delay%26quot%3B%20an%20eviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHouston%20city%20attorneys%20challenged%20the%20state%20law%2C%20arguing%20for%20the%20right%20of%20Texas%20cities%20to%20govern%20themselves%2C%20and%20a%20district%20judge%20agreed%20that%20the%20law%20was%20unconstitutional.%20But%20that%20decision%20is%20stayed%20pending%20appeal%2C%20so%20the%20new%20state%20law%20went%20into%20effect%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Coleman's%20failed%20attempt%20to%20reverse%20the%20lockout%2C%20he%20has%20been%20staying%20with%20an%20uncle%20in%20Houston%2C%20working%20at%20Applebee's%20as%20a%20server.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Dunn%2C%20the%20Atlanta%20mother%2C%20he%20must%20also%20contend%20with%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftexaslawhelp.org%2Farticle%2Fimpact-of-eviction-on-credit-and-future-housing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeviction%20on%20his%20record%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Coleman%20was%20unaware%2C%20until%20BI%20told%20him%2C%20that%20after%20locking%20him%20out%2C%20Texas%20Excel%20filed%20a%20suit%20for%20his%20official%20eviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECourt%20documents%20hint%20at%20why%20he'd%20been%20unaware%20of%20the%20filing.%20A%20server%20noted%20they%20couldn't%20make%20contact%20with%20him%20because%20his%20apartment%20door%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Block-out%20device%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20eviction%20was%20still%20granted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flandlord-illegal-lockout-court-tenant-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720606382000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c7dbf40cf2af6e4f60a07%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flandlord-illegal-lockout-court-tenant-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Most%20remedies%20to%20illegal%20evictions%20offer%20impunity%20to%20landlords%20%E2%80%94%20and%20little%20recourse%20to%20tenants.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22creyes%40insider.com%20(Cecilia%20Reyes)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flandlord-illegal-lockout-court-tenant-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Unprotected%20at%20the%20margins%20of%20the%20rental%20market%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20couple%20standing%20in%20front%20of%20their%20home%20trailer.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c5ec7d1c84a0eaca80d39%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDarlene%20DeLaRoca%20and%20Mike%20Rausch%20at%20their%20former%20home%20outside%20Las%20Vegas%20last%20November.%20Their%20landlord%20cut%20off%20their%20electricity%2C%20DeLaRoca%20said%2C%20and%20then%20evicted%20them.%3Cp%3EBridget%20Bennett%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20Tuesday%20afternoon%20just%20after%20Labor%20Day%20weekend%20in%202020%20and%20a%20flurry%20of%20911%20calls%20were%20coming%20in%20to%20Dekalb%20County%20police%20dispatchers%20from%20the%20Efficiency%20Lodge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20man%20called%20to%20report%20that%20armed%20security%20guards%20were%20being%20aggressive%20toward%20long-staying%20residents%20at%20the%20motel%20in%20Panthersville%2C%20a%20community%20just%20southeast%20of%20Atlanta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20a%20woman%20called%2C%20saying%20she%20lived%20in%20unit%20118%2C%20to%20report%20that%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20are%20being%20kicked%20out%2C%20illegally%20evicted%20without%20notice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20woman%20called%20in%20concerned%20about%20the%20security%20guards%20with%20guns.%20%26quot%3BSomebody%20needs%20to%20come%20take%20control%20of%20this%2C%20because%20it's%20getting%20ridiculous%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20the%20recording.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDekalb%20County%20police%20officers%20arrived%20on%20the%20scene.%20Though%20they'd%20responded%20to%20the%20panicked%20calls%20of%20residents%2C%20the%20officers%20described%20them%20as%20suspects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOfficers%20interviewed%20two%20motel%20residents%20who%20called%20911%3B%20they%20said%20they%20did%20not%20want%20to%20leave%20their%20homes.%20In%20the%20police%20report%2C%20the%20residents%20were%20not%20referred%20to%20as%20tenants%2C%20even%20though%20some%20had%20lived%20there%20for%20over%20a%20year.%20Instead%20they%20were%20recorded%20as%20%26quot%3Bguest%2Fsuspect%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Boffender.%26quot%3B%20Their%20alleged%20debts%2C%20down%20to%20the%20cent%2C%20were%20listed%20next%20to%20their%20names%3A%20one%20woman%20owed%20%242%2C508.70%3B%20one%20man%20%242%2C468.00.%20The%20report%20noted%20that%20the%20motel%20staff%20had%20previously%20warned%20those%20who%20were%20behind%20on%20their%20rent%20that%20they%20would%20change%20the%20locks%20on%20their%20units%20%E2%80%94%20and%20were%20now%20proceeding%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20and%20other%20cases%2C%20whether%20a%20person%20qualifies%20as%20a%20tenant%20would%20prove%20crucial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224019%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20Efficiency%20Lodge%20road%20sign%20saying%20%26quot%3BFree%20Wi-Fi%2C%20Refrigerator%20%26amp%3B%20Stove%20Top%3B%20Vacancy-Move%20In%20Today%3B%20Efficiency%20Lodge%20Weekly%20Specials.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c6d0450b021b5cae9bab9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222679%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Efficiency%20Lodge%2C%20just%20outside%20Atlanta%2C%20was%20home%20to%20multiple%20long-term%20tenants.%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Pointer%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Georgia%2C%20an%20eviction%20requires%20a%20court%20order%2C%20but%20the%20law%20doesn't%20explicitly%20make%20lockouts%20illegal.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20an%20officer%20classified%20the%20incident%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcrime%20against%20property%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20crime%20committed%20by%20the%20residents%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Business%20Insider%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fillegal-wrongful-evictions-law-enforcement-police-court-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestigation%20has%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20in%20cities%20across%20the%20United%20States%2C%20complaints%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.metcouncilonhousing.org%2Fhelp-answers%2Fillegal-evictions-illegal-lockouts%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eillegal%20lockouts%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20on%20the%20rise.%20Most%20states%20require%20landlords%20to%20seek%20a%20judge's%20approval%20before%20removing%20a%20tenant%2C%20a%20process%20that%20gives%20tenants%20a%20chance%20to%20plead%20their%20case%20%E2%80%94%20and%20offers%20them%20notice%20if%20an%20eviction%20is%20approved.%20But%20court%20filings%20and%20911%20calls%20BI%20obtained%20from%20several%20major%20cities%20record%20tenants%20complaining%20of%20landlords%20bypassing%20the%20legal%20process%2C%20instead%20resorting%20to%20tactics%20such%20as%20changing%20the%20locks%20or%20cutting%20off%20utilities%20to%20get%20them%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20in%20informal%20housing%20arrangements%20are%20particularly%20vulnerable%20to%20lockouts%2C%20housing%20advocates%20say%2C%20because%20laws%20in%20many%20states%20leave%20them%20out%20of%20tenant%20protections.%20And%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.flgov.com%2F2024%2F03%2F27%2Fgovernor-desantis-signs-legislation-to-end-the-squatters-scam-in-florida%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewave%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapps.legislature.ky.gov%2Frecord%2F24rs%2Fhb5.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanti-squatter%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.legis.ga.gov%2Fapi%2Flegislation%2Fdocument%2F20232024%2F226032%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaws%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20states%20including%20Florida%2C%20Kentucky%20and%20Georgia%20risks%20muddling%20tenants'%20right%20to%20due%20process%2C%20advocates%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20time%20somebody%20doesn't%20have%20formal%20legal%20protections%20they're%20at%20risk%20of%20others%20taking%20advantage%20of%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Eric%20Tars%2C%20the%20senior%20policy%20director%20at%20the%20National%20Homelessness%20Law%20Center.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20more%20from%20our%20series%20on%20illegal%20evictions%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fillegal-wrongful-evictions-law-enforcement-police-court-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELocked%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flandlord-illegal-lockout-court-tenant-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhen%20renters%20get%20locked%20out%2C%20they%20may%20never%20get%20back%20in%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20outreach%20worker%2C%20Marshall%20Rancifer%20from%20the%20Justice%20for%20All%20Coalition%2C%20arrived%20at%20the%20Efficiency%20Lodge%20that%20afternoon%2C%20hoping%20to%20halt%20the%20removals.%20He%20called%20911%20to%20report%20the%20lockouts%2C%20claiming%20they%20violated%20the%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention's%20new%20COVID%20emergency%20order%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalregister.gov%2Fdocuments%2F2020%2F09%2F04%2F2020-19654%2Ftemporary-halt-in-residential-evictions-to-prevent-the-further-spread-of-covid-19%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Centers%2520for%2520Disease%2520Control%2520and%2520Prevention%2520(CDC)%252C%2520located%2Cfurther%2520spread%2520of%2520COVID%252D19.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebanning%20evictions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Then%20someone%20from%20the%20hotel%20called%20911%20to%20report%20that%20Rancifer%20was%20engaging%20in%20obstruction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolice%20officers%20returned%20to%20the%20motel%2C%20where%20the%20showdown%20had%20escalated.%20Rancifer%20had%20by%20then%20been%20joined%20by%20members%20of%20the%20community%20group%20Housing%20Justice%20League%20and%20local%20journalists.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20Larry%20Johnson%2C%20then%20a%20DeKalb%20County%20commissioner%2C%20had%20called%20on%20Atlanta%20Legal%20Aid%20to%20get%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20got%20over%20there%2C%20I%20was%20like%20in%20a%20war%20zone%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20saw%20people%20with%20vests%20on%20with%20guns.%20I%20saw%20people%20outside%20scrambling%20around%20and%20it%20was%20just%20so%20surreal.%26quot%3B%20In%20the%20midst%20of%20it%20all%2C%20he%20recalled%20seeing%20a%20young%20girl%20playing%20quietly%20with%20her%20toy%20kitchen%20set.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20kicked%20out%20about%20two%20dozen%20families%20that%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lindsey%20Siegel%2C%20an%20attorney%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20case%20for%20Atlanta%20Legal%20Aid.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20traumatic%20event%20for%20the%20community.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDeKalb%20County%20botched%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMillions%20of%20rental%20gray%20zones%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETraumatic%20events%20like%20this%20are%20playing%20out%20across%20the%20nation%2C%20as%20ambiguous%20housing%20arrangements%20have%20become%20more%20common%20in%20the%20face%20of%20a%20national%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jchs.harvard.edu%2Fpress-releases%2Fnew-report-shows-rent-unaffordable-half-renters-cost-burdens-surge-record-levels%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaffordable-housing%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Half%20of%20all%20renters%20in%20the%20US%20spend%20more%20than%2030%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20rent%20and%20utilities%20%E2%80%94%20a%20benchmark%20used%20to%20gauge%20affordability%20%E2%80%94%20pushing%20more%20people%20into%20less%20traditional%20modes%20of%20housing.%20Lacking%20a%20traditional%20written%20lease%20or%20other%20documentation%20of%20their%20status%20as%20renters%2C%20these%20tenants%20exist%20in%20legal%20gray%20zones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202019%20survey%20of%20extended-stay%20motels%20in%20one%20Atlanta%20suburb%2C%20called%20%26quot%3BWhen%20Extended%20Stay%20Becomes%20Home%2C%26quot%3B%20found%20that%20roughly%20a%20third%20catered%20mainly%20to%20travelers%3B%20the%20rest%20were%20primarily%20residential.%20And%20nearly%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20residential%20tenants%20surveyed%20said%20they%20had%20stayed%20there%20for%20a%20year%20or%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Education%20shows%20that%20during%20the%202021-2022%20school%20year%2C%20nearly%20107%2C000%20students%20reported%20hotels%20or%20motels%20as%20a%20primary%20nightly%20residence.%20More%20than%20900%2C000%20reported%20living%20doubled%20up%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20they%20were%20staying%20with%20family%20or%20friends%20without%20being%20named%20on%20a%20lease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20other%20US%20families%20live%20in%20unpermitted%20units%2C%20making%20it%20difficult%20to%20exercise%20their%20rights%20as%20tenants.%20A%202008%20report%20from%20the%20Pratt%20Center%20for%20Community%20Development%20estimated%20114%2C000%20illegal%20rentals%2C%20such%20as%20basement%20apartments%20and%20rooming%20houses%2C%20in%20New%20York%20City%20alone%3B%20in%202014%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20UCLA%20estimated%2050%2C000%20illegal%20backyard%20or%20garage%20units%20just%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Los%20Angeles.%20A%202020%20report%20from%20Freddie%20Mac%20identified%20approximately%201.4%20million%20so-called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freddiemac.com%2Fresearch%2Finsight%2F20200716-identifying-accessory-dwelling-units-from-real-estate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccessory%20dwelling%20units%3C%2Fa%3E%20nationwide%2C%20with%20the%20vast%20majority%20likely%20unpermitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20in%20search%20of%20housing%20have%20settled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.airbnb.com%2Ftravel-revolution-in-data%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elong-term%20into%20Airbnbs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20couple%20posing%20next%20to%20each%20other%20under%20a%20roof%20and%20an%20American%20flag.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c5f4ad1c84a0eaca80d80%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDeLaRoca%20and%20Rausch%20had%20been%20renting%20backyard%20space%20for%20their%20trailer%20in%20unincorporated%20Clark%20County%2C%20Nevada.%20After%20their%20eviction%2C%20they%20ended%20up%20living%20in%20separate%20states.%3Cp%3EBridget%20Bennett%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20locales%20with%20more%20protective%20laws%2C%20tenants%20in%20informal%20or%20unpermitted%20housing%20situations%20may%20think%20twice%20about%20rocking%20the%20boat%2C%20said%20Harrison%20Bohn%2C%20an%20attorney%20at%20the%20Legal%20Aid%20Center%20of%20Southern%20Nevada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20hardest%20part%20about%20people%20who%20live%20in%20these%20really%20odd%20lease%20scenarios%20of%20either%20renting%20a%20room%20or%20renting%20a%20couch%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20that%20if%20you%20do%20want%20to%20start%20a%20process%20of%20enforcing%20your%20rights%2C%20you%20are%20disrupting%20that%20relationship%20with%20your%20landlord.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tagline%20of%20the%20Efficiency%20Lodge%20is%20%26quot%3Bstay%20a%20nite%20or%20stay%20forever.%26quot%3B%20But%20residents%2C%20even%20longtime%20residents%2C%20had%20to%20sign%20a%20contract%20stating%20they%20were%20not%20tenants.%20For%20some%2C%20the%20motel%20was%20their%20only%20home.%20The%20property's%20address%20was%20listed%20on%20residents'%20IDs%3B%20school%20buses%20made%20stops%20at%20the%20motel%20to%20fetch%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20of%20them%20were%20never%20intended%20to%20be%20people's%20homes%2C%26quot%3B%20Charlie%20Bliss%2C%20another%20Atlanta%20Legal%20Aid%20attorney%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20Efficiency%20Lodge%20case%2C%20said%20of%20long-stay%20motels.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20the%20home%20of%20last%20resort%20because%20there%20is%20not%20affordable%20housing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20states%2C%20such%20as%20Nevada%20and%20California%2C%20spell%20out%20when%20a%20resident%20earns%20tenant%20status%20%E2%80%94%20after%2C%20say%2C%2030%20days.%20But%20Georgia's%20regulations%20leave%20room%20for%20ambiguity.%20According%20to%20rules%20governing%20hotels%20and%20motels%2C%20the%20state%20stops%20collecting%20hotel%20taxes%20after%2030%20days%2C%20at%20which%20point%20a%20rental%20becomes%20an%20%26quot%3Bextended%20stay%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20those%20rules%20are%20silent%20on%20whether%20the%20renter%20gains%20the%20protections%20of%20landlord-tenant%20laws.%20A%20statute%20defining%20the%20landlord-tenant%20relationship%20is%20vague%2C%20saying%20it%20begins%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20the%20owner%20of%20real%20estate%20grants%20to%20another%20person%2C%20who%20accepts%20such%20grant%2C%20the%20right%20simply%20to%20possess%20and%20enjoy%26quot%3B%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20how%20the%20police%20handled%20the%20lockouts%20at%20the%20Efficiency%20Lodge%20that%20day%20in%20September%202020%2C%20a%20Dekalb%20County%20spokesperson%2C%20Andrew%20Cauthen%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email%20that%20while%20officers%20told%20two%20people%20they%20were%20trespassing%2C%20they%20%26quot%3Bwere%20not%20arrested%20or%20required%20to%20leave.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrandon%20Turner%2C%20the%20president%20of%20Natson%20Hotel%20Group%2C%20said%20his%20company%20had%20acquired%20this%20and%20other%20Efficiency%20Lodge%20properties%20in%202022.%20He%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20an%20incident%20that%20took%20place%20prior%20to%20the%20purchase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'It%20can't%20be%20obvious%20that%20people%20live%20here'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDarlene%20DeLaRoca%20was%20actually%20hopeful%20when%20she%20attended%20her%20own%20eviction%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20day%20in%20November%202023%2C%20she%20thought%20she'd%20get%20a%20chance%20to%20expose%20what%20she%20saw%20as%20her%20landlord's%20illegal%20pressure%20tactics.%20Instead%2C%20she%20found%20herself%20out%20of%20a%20home%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeLaRoca%20and%20her%20partner%2C%20Mike%20Rausch%2C%20had%20been%20renting%20backyard%20space%20on%20their%20landlord's%20property%20in%20unincorporated%20Clark%20County%2C%20Nevada%2C%20just%20outside%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20for%20at%20least%20three%20months%20at%20that%20point.%20After%20living%20out%20of%20their%20truck%20for%20a%20few%20months%2C%20the%20couple%20said%20they%20traded%20it%20for%20a%20motor%20home%20that%2C%20even%20if%20it%20wouldn't%20run%2C%20got%20them%20closer%20to%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20invested%20over%20a%20thousand%20dollars%20to%20move%2C%20the%20couple%20said%3A%20from%20the%20cost%20of%20towing%20the%20motor%20home%20to%20paying%20the%20deposit%20for%20the%20backyard%20space%20and%20buying%20a%20special%20extension%20cord%20to%20plug%20into%20the%20electricity%20in%20a%20shed%20behind%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20all%20worth%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Rausch%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20getting%20us%20a%20home%20and%20getting%20us%20power%20and%20off%20the%20streets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20lived%20in%20the%20backyard%20with%20their%20dogs%20and%2C%20they%20said%2C%20five%20other%20trailers%20of%20families%20who%20shared%20the%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20holds%20a%20printed%20out%20Facebook%20ad%20of%20trailer%20for%20rent.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c6be3d1c84a0eaca813a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDeLaRoca%20with%20the%20Facebook%20ad%20that%20offered%20her%20and%20her%20partner%20power%2C%20water%2C%20and%20a%20place%20to%20live%20in%20their%20trailer%20for%20%24650%20a%20month.%3Cp%3EBridget%20Bennett%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20had%20found%20the%20listing%20for%20the%20lot%20on%20Facebook%20and%2C%20at%20the%20time%2C%20considered%20it%20a%20godsend%20because%20of%20how%20close%20the%20location%20was%20to%20Rausch's%20work%20at%20Harry%20Reid%20International%20Airport's%20car-return%20center%2C%20less%20than%20an%20hour's%20walk%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20used%20a%20rented%20U-Haul%20as%20their%20main%20form%20of%20transport.%20As%20they%20were%20driving%20back%20from%20a%20Walmart%20run%20one%20day%2C%20DeLaRoca%20said%2C%20police%20officers%20stopped%20them%20in%20front%20of%20the%20landlord's%20house%2C%20saying%20the%20U-Haul%20had%20been%20reported%20as%20stolen.%20The%20couple%2C%20it%20turned%20out%2C%20had%20failed%20to%20return%20it%20on%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20officers%20walked%20into%20the%20property's%20backyard%20and%20saw%20their%20living%20arrangement%2C%20DeLaRoca%20said%2C%20the%20couple's%20relationship%20with%20their%20landlord%2C%20a%20man%20named%20Luis%20Barraza%2C%20soured.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%2C%20Barraza%20told%20them%20they%20had%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20subsequent%20recording%20reviewed%20by%20BI%2C%20DeLaRoca%20asks%20for%20a%20receipt%20for%20%24300%20she%20had%20paid%20toward%20her%20monthly%20rent.%20In%20the%20recording%2C%20a%20man%20she%20identified%20as%20Barraza%20tells%20her%20others%20haven't%20asked%20for%20receipts%20and%20he%20won't%20give%20her%20one.%20After%20telling%20him%20that%20she's%20recording%2C%20DeLaRoca%20asks%20why%20he%20wants%20them%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20established%20some%20rules%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20man%20tells%20her.%20%26quot%3BOne%20thing%20I%20said%20is%20that%20it%20can't%20be%20obvious%20that%20people%20live%20here.%26quot%3B%20In%20unincorporated%20Clark%20County%2C%20where%20the%20property%20is%20located%2C%20operating%20a%20short-term%20rental%20without%20a%20license%20is%20illegal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarraza%20cut%20off%20their%20power%2C%20DeLaRoca%20said%2C%20blaming%20a%20code%20inspection.%20County%20records%20show%20inspectors%20had%20visited%20the%20property%20after%20receiving%20an%20anonymous%20complaint%20that%20the%20owner%20was%20using%20his%20land%20for%20short-term%20rentals%3B%20photos%20they%20took%20document%20at%20least%20half%20a%20dozen%20mobile%20homes%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20records%20make%20no%20note%20of%20inspectors%20asking%20for%20utilities%20to%20be%20discontinued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20black-and-white%20photos%20with%20date%20stamps%20show%20at%20least%20a%20half%20dozen%20trailers%20parked%20on%20a%20rural%20property.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6675f6d865f501a88181586d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELast%20September%2C%20Clark%20County%20inspectors%20photographed%20the%20property%20where%20DeLaRoca%20and%20Rausch%20lived%20in%20a%20trailer.%20DeLaRoca%20said%20her%20landlord%20had%20told%20her%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20can't%20be%20obvious%20that%20people%20live%20here.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EClark%20County%20Building%20%26amp%3B%20Fire%20Prevention%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCode%20Enforcement%20did%20not%20order%20utilities%20to%20be%20disconnected%20in%20this%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20Stacey%20Welling%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Clark%20County%2C%20said%20by%20email.%20She%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bit%20was%20a%20violation%20of%20County%20Code%20to%20reside%20in%20an%20RV%20on%20the%20property%26quot%3B%20but%20that%20Barraza%20was%20not%20fined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarraza%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20DeLaRoca%20brought%20up%20the%20utility%20disconnection%20during%20her%20November%20hearing%20in%20the%20Las%20Vegas%20Justice%20Court%2C%20she%20hoped%20her%20landlord%20would%20be%20held%20accountable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHearing%20Master%20David%20Brown%20told%20her%20their%20situation%20wasn't%20a%20normal%20tenancy%2C%20she%20said.%20But%20he%20still%20issued%20a%20%26quot%3Bno%20cause%26quot%3B%20eviction%20order%3B%20in%20Nevada%2C%20landlords%20don't%20have%20to%20name%20a%20reason.%20DeLaRoca%20and%20Rausch%20had%2010%20days%20to%20move%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELandlords%20are%20generally%20given%20wide%20leeway%20to%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investopedia.com%2Fterms%2Fe%2Feviction.asp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20eviction%20process%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20for%20people%20not%20strictly%20considered%20tenants%2C%20according%20to%20Eric%20Dunn%2C%20the%20director%20of%20litigation%20at%20the%20National%20Housing%20Law%20Project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20the%20property%20is%20not%20a%20space%20that%20somebody%20should%20be%20living%20in%2C%20if%20the%20landlord%20is%20seeking%20to%20remove%20the%20person%20from%20it%2C%20then%20you%20want%20them%20to%20at%20least%20go%20to%20court%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20debate%20over%20what%20constitutes%20a%20tenant%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20battle%20over%20the%20Efficiency%20Lodge%20lasted%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20at%20Atlanta%20Legal%20Aid%20filed%20suit%20in%202020%20on%20behalf%20of%20three%20former%20residents%20who%20were%20locked%20out%20of%20the%20motel%3A%20Armetrius%20Neason%2C%20who%20had%20lived%20there%20continuously%20since%202016%20before%20falling%20behind%20on%20his%20payments%20in%202020%3B%20Lynetrice%20Preston%2C%20who%20had%20lived%20there%20with%20two%20of%20her%20children%20and%20a%20grandchild%20for%20two%20years%2C%20when%20she%20fell%20behind%20on%20her%20weekly%20payments%20after%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foui.doleta.gov%2Funemploy%2Fpdf%2FPUA_FactSheet.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epandemic%20employment%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%20ran%20out%3B%20and%20Altonese%20Weaver%2C%20who%20lived%20at%20the%20motel%20for%20a%20total%20of%2011%20months%20prior%20to%20being%20locked%20out%20in%20July%202020%20after%20she%20fell%20behind%20on%20her%20weekly%20payments%2C%20with%20all%20of%20her%20possessions%20locked%20inside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22778%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tearsheet%20from%20DeKalb%20County%20Police%20Department%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668c0740268f62ba18a80cd9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22223%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20September%202020%2C%20a%20flood%20of%20911%20calls%20came%20in%20from%20the%20Efficiency%20Lodge%20outside%20of%20Atlanta.%20Tenants%20said%20they%20were%20being%20threatened%20and%20locked%20out%3B%20police%20wrote%20them%20up%20as%20suspects.%3Cp%3EDeKalb%20County%20Police%20Department%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20largely%20centered%20on%20the%20ambiguity%20in%20Georgia%20state%20law%3A%20whether%20the%20residents%20were%20tenants%20or%20merely%20guests.%20The%20Legal%20Aid%20lawyers%20argued%20that%20their%20clients%20had%20made%20a%20life%20at%20the%20motel%20and%20that%20it%20was%20illegal%20to%20evict%20them%20without%20going%20before%20a%20judge.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20leave%20families%20susceptible%20to%20being%20locked%20out%20of%20their%20only%20home%20with%20no%20notice%20at%20the%20whim%20of%20a%20landlord%2C%20that's%20a%20very%20troubling%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20Bliss%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20creates%20the%20possibility%20of%20abuse%20and%20exploitation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Efficiency%20Lodge%20had%20high-powered%20representation%20%E2%80%94%20former%20Gov.%20Roy%20Barnes%2C%20whose%20brother%20was%20then%20a%20co-owner%20of%20the%20motel%20chain%2C%20who%20argued%20that%20the%20residents%20were%20just%20like%20any%20other%20inn%20guests%20and%2C%20having%20signed%20a%20contract%20accordingly%2C%20could%20be%20removed%20without%20a%20formal%20eviction%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECourts%20ruled%20in%20the%20residents'%20favor%20in%202021%20and%202022%20and%20ordered%20the%20Efficiency%20Lodge%20to%20file%20an%20eviction%20if%20it%20wanted%20to%20remove%20them.%20But%20Barnes%20appealed%20the%20rulings%20to%20the%20Georgia%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20finally%20issued%20guidance%20in%20June%202023%20on%20what%20constitutes%20a%20landlord-tenant%20relationship%2C%20saying%20it%20hinges%20upon%20a%20person's%20use%20of%20a%20place%20as%20a%20home%2C%20with%20the%20permission%20of%20the%20owner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20questions%2C%20the%20guidance%20states%2C%20are%20dependent%20on%20the%20intent%20of%20both%20parties.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20did%20not%20make%20a%20ruling%20on%20the%20Efficiency%20Lodge%20residents%2C%20remanding%20the%20decision%20back%20to%20a%20lower%20court.%20But%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20laid%20out%20specific%20factors%20for%20courts%20to%20take%20into%20consideration%2C%20such%20as%20the%20length%20of%20time%20someone%20lives%20in%20the%20property%2C%20whether%20they%20routinely%20clean%20their%20unit%2C%20and%20whether%20they%20can%20have%20guests.%20The%20court%20said%20the%20granting%20of%20permission%20to%20occupy%20the%20property%20as%20tenants%20can%20be%20implicit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20settled%20in%20August%202023%20before%20the%20lower%20court%20decided%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20the%20three%20plaintiffs%20qualified%20as%20tenants.%20Bliss%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20settlement%3B%20Barnes%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20to%20his%20law%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELandlords%20and%20loopholes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Nevada%2C%20state%20law%20is%20more%20explicit%2C%20laying%20out%20that%20people%20who%20stay%20in%20a%20hotel%20or%20motel%20for%20more%20than%2030%20days%20gain%20the%20protections%20of%20a%20tenant.%20But%20the%20Desert%20Moon%20Motel%20in%20Las%20Vegas%20appears%20to%20have%20found%20a%20way%20around%20the%20provision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETera%20Strawter%20and%20her%20boyfriend%2C%20Khari%20Varner%2C%20had%20been%20living%20at%20the%20vintage%20downtown%20motel%20for%20nearly%20three%20months%20at%20the%20time%20they%20were%20locked%20out%20in%20October%202023%2C%20far%20longer%20than%20should%20have%20been%20required%20to%20trigger%20the%20status%20change.%20During%20that%20time%2C%20she%20gave%20birth%20to%20twins%2C%20the%20couple%20said%20in%20a%20court%20complaint.%20All%20of%20their%20possessions%20were%20inside%2C%20Strawter%20said%2C%20including%20her%20medications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20night%20of%20the%20lockout%2C%20Varner%20said%2C%20he%20and%20Strawter%20managed%20to%20get%20back%20into%20the%20room%20and%20slept%20there.%20The%20next%20day%2C%20Strawter%20took%20to%20Facebook%20to%20livestream%20at%20least%20two%20law-enforcement%20officers%20as%20they%20arrested%20Varner%20after%20telling%20the%20couple%20to%20leave%20the%20unit.%20Police%20officers%20stood%20by%20as%20a%20motel%20representative%20read%20Strawter%20a%20statement%20warning%20her%20that%20she%20would%20be%20considered%20a%20trespasser%20and%20would%20be%20arrested%20if%20she%20came%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVarner%20filed%20two%20complaints%20with%20the%20Las%20Vegas%20Justice%20Court%2C%20claiming%20the%20Desert%20Moon%20had%20illegally%20evicted%20them.%20The%20second%20complaint%2C%20which%20BI%20obtained%2C%20asserts%20that%20the%20couple%20had%20been%20living%20at%20the%20motel%20for%20almost%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20detail%20would%20prove%20critical%20as%20the%20couple%20fought%20the%20motel%20in%20court%3A%20They%20had%20received%20financial%20help%20from%20two%20different%20nonprofit%20agencies%20%E2%80%94%20Puentes%20Las%20Vegas%20and%20Lutheran%20Social%20Services%20of%20Nevada%20%E2%80%94%20which%20had%20each%20paid%20for%2028-day%20stays%2C%20Strawter%20said%2C%20before%20she%20and%20Varner%20took%20over%20the%20weekly%20payments%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22745%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20complaint%20against%20a%20downtown%20Las%20Vegas%20motel%2C%20the%20Desert%20Moon.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668c0770268f62ba18a80cf3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22595%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20November%202023%2C%20Khari%20Varner%20filed%20a%20complaint%20against%20a%20downtown%20Las%20Vegas%20motel%2C%20the%20Desert%20Moon%2C%20saying%20he%20and%20his%20fiancee%20had%20been%20illegally%20locked%20out.%3Cp%3ELas%20Vegas%20Justice%20Court%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPuentes'%20president%2C%20Guy%20Girardin%2C%20declined%20to%20confirm%20details%20of%20this%20case%20but%20said%20the%20organization%20does%20provide%20housing%20assistance%20and%20sometimes%20refers%20people%20to%20extended-stay%20motels.%20He%20said%20the%20group%20caps%20its%20payments%20at%2028%20days%20at%20the%20request%20of%20the%20motels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPuentes%20has%20seen%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20people%20who%20have%20made%20homes%20at%20extended%20stays%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20Girardin%20said%2C%20turning%20a%20model%20once%20geared%20to%20business%20travelers%20to%20%26quot%3Balmost%20100%25%20housing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20sat%20in%20on%20the%20couple's%20hearings%20over%20the%20complaint.%20The%20first%20hearing%20ended%20quickly%20after%20a%20judge%20ruled%20that%20Varner%20had%20failed%20to%20give%20Desert%20Moon%20proper%20notice%2C%20a%20common%20occurrence%20with%20tenant-lockout%20complaints%2C%20according%20to%20a%20sample%20of%20outcomes%20BI%20examined%20and%20hearings%20one%20reporter%20attended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20plaque%20listing%20the%20Justice%20Court%20eviction%20room%20No.%201D.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667da66cd1c84a0eaca86637%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20hearing%20room%20at%20the%20Regional%20Justice%20Center%20in%20Las%20Vegas.%20Nevada%20offers%20tenants%20a%20speedy%20pathway%20for%20fighting%20a%20lockout.%3Cp%3EBridget%20Bennett%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20second%20hearing%20over%20the%20lockout%2C%20in%20November%2C%20the%20couple%20explained%20to%20Brown%2C%20the%20hearing%20master%2C%20that%20they%20had%20been%20living%20in%20the%20motel%20since%20August%20through%20a%20variety%20of%20payment%20structures.%20First%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20room%20was%20covered%20by%20one%20nonprofit%2C%20then%20another%2C%20and%20then%20the%20stay%20rolled%20over%20into%20their%20names.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20motel's%20owner%2C%20Brian%20Michael%20Schwalbe%2C%20said%20he%20thought%20the%20couple%20had%20agreed%20to%20leave.%20The%20couple%20countered%20that%20they%20had%20verbally%20told%20the%20motel%20of%20their%20intent%20to%20stay%20for%20at%20least%2090%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Brown%20said%20continued%20occupancy%20of%20the%20motel%20would%20make%20them%20tenants%2C%20Schwalbe%20said%20he%20thought%20the%20payments%20from%20other%20entities%20would%20change%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20really%20grappling%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20you've%20been%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Brown%20said%20to%20the%20couple%2C%20adding%20that%20if%20they%20had%20proof%20they%20had%20personally%20paid%20for%20even%20two%20days%20after%20their%20last%2C%20self-funded%2C%2028-day%20stay%2C%20he%20would%20rule%20in%20their%20favor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVarner%20started%20to%20cry.%20The%20couple%20could%20not%20provide%20proof%20of%20payment%2C%20Strawter%20later%20told%20BI%2C%20because%20they%20had%20paid%20in%20cash.%20Brown%20denied%20their%20petition%2C%20stating%20their%20relationship%20with%20the%20Desert%20Moon%20didn't%20qualify%20as%20a%20landlord-tenant%20one%20under%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20sorry%2C%20it's%20not%20fun%20for%20the%20judge%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENatalie%20Bergevin%2C%20the%20manager%20of%20Desert%20Moon%2C%20said%20the%20motel%20always%20considered%20Strawter%20and%20Varner%20as%20short-term%20guests%2C%20not%20tenants.%20Though%20the%20couple%20had%20stayed%20for%20more%20than%20a%20month%2C%20the%20motel's%20agreement%20was%20with%20the%20paying%20agencies%2C%20not%20with%20Strawter%20and%20Varner%2C%20she%20said.%20Bergevin%20said%20they%20had%20each%20signed%20written%20agreements%20that%20they%20would%20not%20be%20considered%20tenants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20weren't%20locked%20out%2C%20she%20added%3B%20their%20key%20was%20simply%20deactivated.%20She%20insisted%2C%20as%20Schwalbe%20had%20in%20court%2C%20that%20the%20couple%20had%20previously%20agreed%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLong-term%20residency%20is%20never%20our%20intention%2C%26quot%3B%20Bergevin%20said%2C%20calling%20the%20situation%20%26quot%3Btruly%20unpleasant%20and%20unfortunate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMatthew%20Main%20is%20an%20attorney%20who%20has%20represented%20residents%20in%20similarly%20precarious%20housing%20situations%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20where%20state%20law%20also%20grants%20residents%20tenants'%20rights%20after%2030%20days.%20He%20said%20courts%20had%20become%20overly%20restrictive%20about%20whom%20tenant%20laws%20cover%2C%20making%20them%20less%20effective%20at%20preserving%20housing%20stability%20than%20at%20protecting%20the%20economic%20interests%20of%20landlords.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRemoving%20someone%20from%20their%20home%20is%20a%20violent%20act%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20public%20officials%20shouldn't%20tolerate%20landlord%20gamesmanship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMain%20said%20he%20had%20seen%20hearings%20about%20illegal%20evictions%20of%20residents%20in%20%26quot%3Bshady%20gray%20areas%20of%20housing%26quot%3B%20get%20bogged%20down%20in%20fights%20over%20whether%20residents%20are%20tenants%20under%20the%20law.%20%26quot%3BThe%20litigation%20should%20take%20five%20minutes%3A%20Was%20this%20person%20there%20with%20permission%3F%20That's%20the%20end%20of%20the%20question%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20these%20proceedings%20become%20so%20lengthy%20is%20occupants%20have%20to%20litigate%20their%20status.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMakeshift%20rooming%20houses%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20Panusky%2C%20an%20attorney%20in%20Atlanta%20who%20represents%20tenants%20in%20unlawful-eviction%20cases%2C%20said%20he%20had%20been%20getting%20more%20calls%20lately%20from%20people%20living%20in%20unlicensed%20makeshift%20rooming%20houses.%20And%20Sara%20Heymann%2C%20a%20community%20activist%20with%20%C3%9Anete%2C%20a%20volunteer-led%20housing%20advocacy%20group%20in%20Chicago%2C%20said%20rooming%20houses%20had%20also%20become%20more%20common%20in%20her%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20single-family%20home%20in%20Chicago's%20Roseland%20neighborhood%2C%20converted%20into%20a%2016-unit%20rooming%20house%2C%20illustrates%20how%20these%20illegal%20conversions%20increase%20tenants'%20vulnerability.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20lacking%20formal%20leases%2C%20the%20tenants%20were%20even%20accused%20of%20being%20squatters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202022%2C%20the%20landlord%2C%20Go%20Home%20LLC%2C%20filed%20for%20eviction%20against%20one%20named%20resident%20along%20with%20%26quot%3Ball%20unknown%20occupants%26quot%3B%20of%20its%20%26quot%3Bsingle%20family%20home%26quot%3B%20and%20was%20granted%20an%20eviction%20through%20the%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20obtained%20bodycam%20footage%20of%20what%20followed%3A%20two%20attempts%20by%20the%20Cook%20County%20Sheriff's%20Office%20to%20execute%20the%20eviction%20on%20what%20they%20discovered%20was%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20a%20single%20family%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22On%20the%20left%2C%20an%20image%20of%20a%20law%20enforcement%20officer%20pointing%20a%20flashlight%20at%20doors%20labeled%20%26quot%3B1%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3B2%26quot%3B%3B%20on%20the%20right%20the%20exterior%20of%20a%20single-family%20home.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6675f7e665f501a88181587b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESheriff's%20officers%20entered%20a%20single%20family%20home%20on%20Chicago's%20South%20Side%20in%20February%202023%20to%20evict%20a%20tenant.%20Their%20body%20cameras%20documented%20signs%20that%20it%20was%20being%20used%20as%20a%20rooming%20house.%3Cp%3ECook%20County%20Sheriff's%20Office%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20first%20attempt%2C%20in%20February%202023%2C%20the%20footage%20shows%20several%20rooms%20connected%20by%20a%20long%20hallway%2C%20each%20door%20bearing%20a%20number.%20%26quot%3BYou%20know%20I've%20had%20a%20problem%20with%20him%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20officer%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20he%20told%20us%20it%20was%20one%20house%20and%20there%20were%20separate%20rooms.%26quot%3B%20The%20officers%20departed%20without%20removing%20anyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20months%20later%2C%20the%20sheriff's%20office%20made%20a%20second%20eviction%20attempt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20time%2C%20a%20representative%20of%20the%20landlord%20assured%20the%20officers%20that%20individual%20rooms%20were%20not%20being%20rented%20out%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20go%20in%20there%2C%20and%20it's%20numbered%2C%20turn%20right%20the%20fuck%20back%20around%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20officer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20room%20they%20checked%20was%20small%2C%20with%20only%20one%20window.%20In%20the%20video%2C%20the%20bed%20was%20pushed%20to%20the%20end%20of%20the%20room%20and%20toys%20were%20strewn%20all%20over%20the%20floor.%20This%20time%2C%20only%20remnants%20of%20the%20numbers%20were%20visible%20on%20the%20doors%3B%20a%20resident%20later%20told%20a%20deputy%20the%20owner%20took%20down%20the%20numbers%20just%20hours%20before%20the%20deputies%20showed%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%20an%20officer%20asks%2C%20%26quot%3BDoes%20anyone%20have%20a%20rental%20agreement%3F%20A%20lease%3F%26quot%3B%20But%20no%20one%20appears%20to%20have%20one%3B%20one%20resident%20says%20he%20has%20text%20messages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lead%20officer%20calls%20off%20the%20eviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can't%20pick%20apart%20the%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Michael%20Duckworth%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Go%20Home%2C%20which%20manages%20the%20property.%20%26quot%3BThe%20way%20that%20you%20guys%20are%20going%20about%20this%20is%20just%20really%20illegal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuckworth%20told%20BI%20that%20he'd%20described%20the%20property%20in%20court%20as%20a%20single-family%20home%20on%20the%20advice%20of%20counsel%20but%20that%20in%20fact%20%26quot%3Beach%20room%20was%20its%20own%20entity.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20that%20while%20he%20didn't%20usually%20offer%20traditional%20leases%2C%20the%20sheriff's%20officers%20declined%20to%20evict%20only%20because%20the%20occupants%20were%20colluding%20to%20create%20confusion.%20%26quot%3BBasically%2C%20if%20there's%20anything%20that%20looks%20like%20it%20may%20be%20off%20a%20little%20bit%20or%20if%20they're%20not%20100%25%20sure%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey're%20kind%20of%20tasked%20to%20call%20it%20off.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20wanted%20the%20residents%20out%20because%2C%20he%20claimed%2C%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Bmaliciously%20refusing%20to%20pay%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20company%20had%20%26quot%3Blost%20control%20of%20the%20house.%26quot%3B%20But%20he%20insists%20he%20handled%20the%20eviction%20by%20the%20book%20and%20did%20everything%20legally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20empty%20family-style%20house.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c6b2750b021b5cae9b94e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20renovated%20interior%20of%20the%20informal%20Chicago%20rooming%20house%20after%20it%20was%20vacated%20over%20building%20safety%20concerns.%3Cp%3EAbel%20Uribe%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMatthew%20Walberg%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20sheriff's%20office%2C%20said%20Go%20Home%20failed%20to%20properly%20serve%20notice%20to%20the%20home's%20occupants.%20%26quot%3BThe%20order%20for%20eviction%20did%20not%20describe%20the%20property%20as%20it%20was%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20all%20these%20multiple%20units%20and%20officers%20couldn't%20enforce%26quot%3B%20the%20eviction%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%20of%20last%20year%2C%20Go%20Home%20filed%20a%20new%20motion%20asking%20for%20emergency%20intervention%2C%20claiming%20all%20of%20the%20tenants%20were%20squatters.%20The%20judge%20denied%20it.%20He%20pointed%20out%20that%20Duckworth%2C%20representing%20himself%20as%20the%20landlord's%20agent%2C%20had%20admitted%20that%20several%20tenants%20had%20rented%20from%20him%20at%20other%20properties%2C%20casting%20doubt%20on%20his%20claim%20that%20everyone%20at%20the%20property%20was%20a%20squatter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20eviction%20order%2C%20however%2C%20remained%20in%20place.%20Ultimately%2C%20the%20City%20of%20Chicago%20vacated%20the%20home%20over%20building%20safety%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeft%20living%20under%20a%20freeway%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20their%20hearing%20last%20November%2C%20Darlene%20DeLaRoca%20and%20Mike%20Rausch%20faced%20a%2010-day%20deadline%20to%20vacate%20their%20trailer%20home%20outside%20Las%20Vegas.%20That%20wasn't%20much%20time%20given%20that%20the%20trailer%20still%20wasn't%20working%20and%20they'd%20have%20to%20repair%20it%20before%20they%20could%20move.%20If%20they%20weren't%20out%20by%20then%2C%20the%20court-ordered%20eviction%20meant%20a%20county%20constable%20would%20remove%20them%20by%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20DeLaRoca%20wasn't%20ready%20to%20give%20up.%20Instead%20of%20using%20their%20savings%20to%20pay%20for%20a%20tow%20or%20repair%20the%20trailer%2C%20she%20told%20BI%2C%20she%20and%20Rausch%20decided%20to%20pay%20a%20bond%20of%20%24250%20to%20appeal%20their%20eviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20an%20attorney%2C%20DeLaRoca%20said%2C%20she%20had%20trouble%20figuring%20out%20the%20paperwork%20and%20wasn't%20sure%20whether%20she%20had%20filed%20the%20appeal%20correctly.%20She%20worried%20she%20had%20doomed%20their%20chances%20of%20being%20heard%20by%20a%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20constable's%20visit%20loomed.%20On%20nights%20she%20couldn't%20sleep%2C%20depressed%20about%20the%20prospect%20of%20spending%20Thanksgiving%20on%20the%20streets%2C%20she'd%20work%20on%20drafting%20a%20post%20for%20a%20GoFundMe.%20%26quot%3BThe%20judge%20says%20we%20need%20to%20be%20out%20in%2010%20days%2C%20we%20don't%20have%20enough%20money%20to%20move%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20and%20Rausch%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIn%2010%20days%20we%20will%20be%20homeless.%20We%20are%20asking%20for%20help%2C%20because%20if%20this%20landlord%20can%20do%20this%20to%20our%20family%20and%205%20other%20families%20and%20get%20away%20with%20it%2C%20he%20will%20do%20it%20to%20other%20families.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20day%20the%20constables%20came%2C%20DeLaRoca%20said%2C%20everything%20went%20wrong.%20They%20had%20been%20able%20to%20pack%20some%20things%20but%2C%20in%20the%20shuffle%2C%20left%20their%20bags%20inside%2C%20along%20with%20the%20motor%20home's%20keys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Inside%20of%20a%20trailer%2C%20a%20white-erase%20board%20that%20hangs%20on%20the%20wall%2C%20displays%20encouraging%20messages.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667c697ad1c84a0eaca81237%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20interior%20of%20DeLaRoca%20and%20Rausch's%20trailer.%20The%20day%20of%20their%20eviction%2C%20they%20lost%20almost%20all%20of%20their%20possessions.%3Cp%3EBridget%20Bennett%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20left%20with%20the%20clothes%20on%20our%20backs%2C%26quot%3B%20DeLaRoca%20said%20by%20email%20shortly%20after%20they%20were%20put%20out.%20%26quot%3BI%20should%20have%20been%20more%20prepared.%20It's%20my%20own%20fault%2C%20but%20it's%20kind%20of%20hard%20when%20you're%20not%20really%20sure%20what%20you're%20doing%20or%20have%20the%20means%20to%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20didn't%20have%20even%20a%20day's%20worth%20of%20food%20for%20them%20or%20their%20two%20dogs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20removal%20upended%20their%20lives.%20The%20pair%20spent%20some%20nights%20under%20a%20freeway%20overpass%3B%20some%20days%2C%20they%20resorted%20to%20panhandling%20for%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20they%20separated.%20On%20Christmas%20Day%2C%20Rausch%20sent%20Business%20Insider%20a%20text%20message.%20It%20was%20to