nd's%20upbringing%20was%20strict%20and%20punishment-heavy.%20He%20has%20distinct%20memories%20of%20hearing%20%26quot%3BStop%20crying%2C%20or%20I'll%20give%20you%20something%20to%20cry%20about%26quot%3B%20frequently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20personal%20experience%2C%20fear-based%2C%20punitive%20parenting%20does%20not%20lead%20to%20healthy%20adults%20who%20can%20manage%20their%20emotions%20well.%20That's%20why%20respectful%20and%20empathic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-gentle-parenting-making-me-a-pushover-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egentle%20parenting%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20acknowledged%20a%20child's%20feelings%20had%20a%20real%20appeal%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cc84f35a-1f75-4caf-88a9-0946f835235a%5C%22%3EI%20looked%20into%20gentle%20parenting%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20in%20my%20daughter's%20life%2C%20I%20started%20following%20gentle%20parenting%20influencers.%20This%20included%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-little-feelings-parenting-technique-isnt-realistic-for-me-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBig%20Little%20Feelings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20debuted%20on%20Instagram%20just%20as%20we%20were%20entering%20the%20difficult%20toddler%20years.%20Although%20I%20had%20years%20of%20experience%20working%20with%20children%2C%20my%20daughter's%20meltdowns%20felt%20overwhelming%20and%20unmanageable.%20I%20didn't%20like%20the%20concept%20of%20time-outs%2C%20and%20I%20also%20didn't%20like%20how%20frustrated%20her%20explosive%20reactions%20made%20me%20feel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20purchased%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-how-prevent-toddler-tantrums-big-little-feelings-experts-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBig%20Little%20Feeling's%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BWinning%20the%20Toddler%20Stage%26quot%3B%20course%20in%20the%20hopes%20of%20discovering%20the%20magic%20words%20to%20say%20to%20tame%20my%20daughter's%20tantrums%2C%20as%20they%20said.%20I%20hoped%20learning%20the%20scripts%20they%20provided%20would%20transform%20my%20daughter%20into%20a%20more%20cooperative%20toddler%20and%20me%20into%20a%20calmer%2C%20more%20patient%20mom.%20But%20even%20though%20I%20watched%20all%20the%20videos%20and%20tried%20to%20implement%20their%20advice%2C%20most%20of%20it%20didn't%20seem%20to%20work%20with%20my%20daughter.%20And%20OKing%20her%20feelings%20started%20to%20feel%20ridiculous%20after%20a%20while.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20big%20influencer%20whose%20advice%20I%20tried%20to%20follow%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdr-becky-why-parents-yell-repair-attachment-theory-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Becky%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20waited%20months%20for%20her%20book%20to%20be%20available%20from%20the%20library.%20The%20waitlist%20was%20so%20long%20I%20ended%20up%20with%20the%20audiobook.%20I%20spent%20hours%20listening%20to%20techniques%20that%20I%20tried%20to%20implement%20(unsuccessfully)%20with%20my%20daughter%2C%20some%20of%20which%20seemed%20to%20make%20her%20more%20upset.%20I%20couldn't%20figure%20out%20what%20I%20was%20doing%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20the%20end%20of%20the%20book%2C%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdr-becky-kennedys-tips-for-dealing-with-kids-feelings-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Becky%3C%2Fa%3E%20admitted%20that%20the%20behavioral%20techniques%20she%20discussed%20in%20the%20book%20weren't%20effective%20with%20neurodivergent%20children.%20Eight%20hours%20wasted%20(and%20many%20bops%20from%20a%20dysregulated%2C%20angry%20child)%20on%20a%20book%20that%20wasn't%20even%20written%20for%20her.%20I%20was%20pissed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22677b9bb2-e168-4f2e-bfac-ef59c956026c%5C%22%3EI%20thought%20I%20was%20the%20problem%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20several%20years%20of%20trying%20to%20gentle%20parent%20in%20the%20style%20of%20influencers%20like%20Big%20Little%20Feelings%20and%20Dr.%20Becky%2C%20I%20had%20started%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20problem%20was%20me.%20If%20I%20couldn't%20make%20their%20expert%20advice%20work%2C%20then%20obviously%20I%20was%20just%20a%20bad%20mom.%20Eventually%2C%20I%20discovered%20that%20the%20disconnect%20was%20that%20my%20daughter%20is%20autistic.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20advice%20developed%20for%20neurotypical%20children%20was%20usually%20not%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20frustrating%20thing%20is%20that%20these%20influencers%20seem%20to%20be%20selling%20one-size-fits-all%20behavioral%20techniques%20when%20there%20is%20no%20such%20thing%2C%20especially%20with%20neurodivergent%20children.%20Even%20with%20neurotypical%20children%2C%20there%20is%20no%20one-size-fits-all%20way%20to%20deal%20with%20difficult%20behaviors.%20The%20rigidity%20of%20that%20seems%20to%20harken%20back%20to%20the%20strict%20way%20of%20parenting%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20grew%20up%20with%20that%20refuses%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20every%20child%20is%20an%20individual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20changed%20how%20I%20parent%20her.%20Since%20my%20daughter%20thrives%20on%20consistency%20and%20is%20very%20focused%20on%20schedules%20and%20time%2C%20we%20try%20to%20keep%20things%20as%20structured%20as%20possible%20for%20her%2C%20which%20recently%20has%20meant%20implementing%20a%20visual%20schedule%20and%20timer.%20Although%20it's%20incredibly%20frustrating%20sometimes%2C%20she%20might%20not%20react%20in%20the%20same%20way%20to%20something%20that%20she%20did%20yesterday%2C%20and%20we%20have%20to%20be%20flexible%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20I'm%20not%20sure%20what%20label%20I'd%20put%20on%20my%20parenting%20style%2C%20perhaps%20mostly%20authoritative%2C%20a%20parenting%20style%20that%20is%20more%20focused%20on%20being%20responsive%20and%20supportive%20while%20still%20setting%20boundaries.%20Sometimes%20it%20feels%20like%20we%20are%20throwing%20things%20against%20the%20wall%20and%20seeing%20what%20sticks.%