ps%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftheme-parks-dynamic-pricing-legoland-madame-tussauds-merlin-entertainments-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edynamic%20pricing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20creeping%20across%20the%20economy.%20Want%20to%20know%20what%20your%20Uber%20ride%20or%20concert%20ticket%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurge-pricing-increasingly-being-used-at-restaurants-and-theaters-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebowling-alley%20visit%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20going%20to%20run%20you%3F%20It%20depends!%20Even%20Walmart%20is%20testing%20out%20digital%20price%20tags%2C%20which%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporate.walmart.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F06%2F06%2Fnew-tech-better-outcomes-digital-shelf-labels-are-a-win-for-customers-and-associates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esays%3C%2Fa%3E%20make%20life%20easier%20for%20associates%20and%20improve%20the%20customer%20experience.%20There's%20been%20speculation%20that%20the%20tags%20could%20be%20used%20for%20variable%20pricing%2C%20though%20Walmart%20says%20its%20%26quot%3Bevery%20day%20low%20price%26quot%3B%20strategy%20isn't%20changing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20changes%20add%20up%20to%20one%20pervasive%20sensation%3A%20America%20is%20suffering%20from%20a%20major%20case%20of%20price%20fatigue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20incredibly%20frustrating%20not%20to%20know%20what%20anything%20costs%2C%20and%20the%20situation%20is%20only%20getting%20worse.%20While%20inflation%20is%20cooling%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstores-cutting-prices-summer-list-walmart-target-amazon-aldi-walgreens-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn%20of%20discounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20mean%20a%20reversion%20to%20pre-pandemic%20prices.%20People%20are%20still%20on%20edge%20that%20high%20inflation%20could%20rear%20its%20ugly%20head%20again.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-quietly-picking-your-pocket-with-personalized-pricing-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euse%20of%20surge%20pricing%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20extra%20anxiety-inducing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20going%20to%20introduce%20something%20that's%20new%20and%20that%20may%20give%20a%20pause%20or%20a%20hesitation%2C%20you%20might%20not%20want%20to%20necessarily%20do%20it%20when%20people%20are%20very%20price%20sensitive%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Carly%20Fink%2C%20the%20head%20of%20research%20and%20strategy%20at%20Provoke%20Insights%2C%20a%20market-research%20company.%20%26quot%3BIf%20it%20was%20a%20great%20economy%20and%20everyone%20felt%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20yeah%2C%20I%20have%20the%20money%20to%20spend%2C'%20I%20would%20assume%20they%20would%20be%20less%20nervous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20goes%20without%20saying%20that%20inflation%20has%20been%20a%20problem%20in%20recent%20years.%20The%20consumer%20price%20index%20is%20up%20by%20more%20than%2020%25%20since%20February%202020.%20Financially%20and%20psychologically%2C%20it's%20a%20pain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20wages%20don't%20rise%20along%20with%20inflation%2C%20it%20hurts%20people's%20buying%20power%20and%20forces%20them%20to%20change%20their%20budgets%20and%20spending%20habits.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F1_Stantcheva_unembargoed.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELow-income%20people%20in%20particular%20suffer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20workers%20blame%20their%20employers'%20greed%20for%20their%20wages%20not%20budging.%20Even%20when%20pay%20does%20rise%20with%20prices%2C%20everything%20costing%20more%20still%20feels%20like%20a%20loss.%20Inflation%20is%20stressful%2C%20and%20it%20can%20make%20planning%20extra%20challenging.%20If%20prices%20are%20going%20up%2C%20how%20are%20you%20supposed%20to%20know%20how%20much%20money%20you%20need%20to%20save%20for%20your%20next%20vacation%20%E2%80%94%20let%20alone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-social-security-gen-z-millennials-uncertainty-fears-pensions-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estash%20away%20for%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20even%20as%20inflation%20settles%20down%2C%20the%20tool%20employed%20to%20fight%20it%20%E2%80%94%20higher%20interest%20rates%20%E2%80%94%20adds%20another%20layer%20of%20uncertainty.%20If%20you're%20in%20the%20market%20for%20a%20house%2C%20it's%20tough%20to%20gauge%20whether%20you%20ought%20to%20wait%20for%20mortgage%20rates%20to%20come%20back%20down%20or%20whether%20you%20should%20pull%20the%20trigger%20now.%20It's%20a%20similar%20story%20if%20you're%20in%20the%20market%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fbusiness%2Fautos%2Fcar-prices-are-declining-buyers-arent-seeing-it-9ca51d12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20car%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20prices%20have%20come%20down%20some%20but%20interest%20rates%20have%20not%2C%20and%20it's%20hard%20to%20know%20what%20the%20right%20move%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFink%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprovokeinsights.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2FProvoke-Insights_Summer2024_Economy.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eher%20surveys%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicate%20that%20even%20though%20inflation%20is%20calming%2C%20consumers%20are%20still%20nervous%20about%20it%2C%20with%20nearly%20two-thirds%20ranking%20it%20in%20April%20as%20one%20of%20their%20top%20two%20concerns.%20A%20similar%20proportion%20said%20they'd%20become%20more%20budget-conscious%20than%20they%20were%20six%20months%20earlier.%20We're%20looking%20at%20a%20very%20%26quot%3Bprice%20sensitive%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bworried%26quot%3B%20consumer%2C%20she%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20hard%20for%20them%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20everything%20that's%20happening.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20relatively%20small-ticket%20items%20can%20come%20with%20a%20price%20tag%20that%20provokes%20a%20sense%20of%20whiplash.%20A%20%26quot%3Bgood%26quot%3B%20price%20for%20something%20today%20may%20have%20seemed%20outlandish%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20it's%20understandable%20to%20wonder%20whether%20today's%20price%20is%20just%20as%20fleeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20absolutely%20understand%20shoppers%20who%20have%20price%20fatigue.%20It%20just%20beats%20you%20down%2C%20and%20certain%20commodities%20have%20increased%20so%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jon%20Hauptman%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20president%20of%20Price%20Dimensions%2C%20a%20retail%20consultancy.%20%26quot%3BThink%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpepsico-pepsi-high-prices-putting-off-us-shoppers-sales-america-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecarbonated%20soft%20drinks%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20whole%20idea%20of%20what's%20a%20good%20price%20for%20a%2012-pack%20of%20carbonated%20soft%20drinks%20has%20changed%20dramatically%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumers%20tend%20to%20be%20price%20sensitive%2C%20meaning%20their%20buying%20behaviors%20change%20as%20prices%20go%20up%20or%20down%2C%20though%20they're%20not%20very%20price%20aware.%20Most%20people%20can%20name%20the%20specific%20prices%20of%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20things%20at%20the%20grocery%20store%20that%20they%20buy%20all%20the%20time%2C%20like%20milk%20or%20eggs.%20Overall%2C%20however%2C%20they%20intuitively%20sense%20that%20prices%20are%20increasing%2C%20and%20broad-based%20inflation%20means%20purchases%20big%20and%20small%20require%20a%20second%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20forces%20shoppers%20to%20shop%20more%20carefully%2C%26quot%3B%20Hauptman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20proliferation%20of%20dynamic%20pricing%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20prices%20that%20fluctuate%20based%20on%20market%20conditions%20such%20as%20supply%20and%20demand%20%E2%80%94%20makes%20the%20landscape%20harder%20to%20navigate.%20The%20prices%20of%20a%20variety%20of%20products%20and%20services%20aren't%20just%20different%20from%20what%20they%20were%20a%20year%20ago%3B%20they%20may%20be%20different%20from%20what%20they%20were%20a%20day%20ago%20or%20even%20a%20few%20minutes%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDynamic%20pricing%20isn't%20new.%20For%20better%20or%20for%20worse%2C%20it's%20well%20established%20in%20some%20industries.%20People%20have%20long%20been%20used%20to%20it%20when%20they're%20booking%20flights%20or%20hotels%2C%20for%20example.%20It%20can%20make%20sense%20in%20some%20of%20these%20settings%2C%20like%20hospitality%2C%20said%20Timothy%20Webb%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20hospitality%20business%20management%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Delaware%20who's%20worked%20on%20pricing%20strategies%20for%20sports%20teams%20and%20tourism%20spots.%20%26quot%3BIt%20really%20centers%20around%20the%20perishable%20nature%20of%20the%20product%20and%20that%20its%20capacity%20is%20constrained%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20A%20hotel%20can't%20store%20up%20more%20rooms%20to%20rent%20out%20during%20the%20summer%2C%20so%20raising%20prices%20for%20peak%20times%20lets%20it%20stay%20afloat%20all%20year%2C%20financially%2C%20and%20may%20help%20prevent%20overcrowding.%20Conversely%2C%20dropping%20prices%20during%20the%20slow%20season%20means%20it's%20not%20sitting%20empty%20all%20winter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20nobody%20%3Cem%3Elikes%20%3C%2Fem%3Epaying%20extra%20for%20a%20Christmas%20flight%20or%20their%20summer%20hotel%20room.%20Yes%2C%20happy%20hours%20and%20early-bird%20specials%20have%20been%20around%20forever%2C%20but%20the%20idea%20of%20paying%20extra%20for%20a%20restaurant%20reservation%20or%20meal%20during%20busy%20times%20is%20not%20great.%20The%20supply-demand%20forces%20that%20make%20peak-time%20Ubers%20outrageously%20expensive%20or%20Taylor%20Swift%20tickets%20prohibitively%20pricey%20may%20be%20real%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20consumers%20feel%20they%20are%20fair%20or%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20often%20interpret%20dynamic%20pricing%20as%20a%20mechanism%20for%20companies%20to%20maximize%20profits.%20Provoke%20Insights'%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprovokeinsights.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FProvoke-Insights_Summer2024_Restaurant.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20most%20consumers%20still%20aren't%20super%20familiar%20with%20the%20concept%2C%20but%20when%20asked%20what%20they%20would%20do%20if%20a%20restaurant%20they%20visit%20implements%20it%2C%20two-thirds%20say%20they%20would%20eat%20there%20less%20often.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcivicscience.com%2Fconsumer-understanding-of-dynamic-pricing-is-not-always-accurate-and-qsr-brands-should-take-note%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20consumer%20analytics%20platform%20CivicScience%20found%20that%20a%20majority%20of%20consumers%20say%20they%20agree%20with%20the%20statement%20that%20dynamic%20pricing%20is%20%26quot%3Bprice%20gouging.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20focusing%20on%20getting%20a%20discount%20when%20they%20pop%20into%20Starbucks%20during%20a%20slow%20period%2C%20people%20think%20about%20the%20experience%20of%20trying%20to%20order%20a%20Lyft%20in%20the%20rain.%20They're%20not%20wrong%20to%20feel%20this%20way%20%E2%80%94%20making%20money%20is%20how%20companies%20talk%20about%20their%20pricing%20choices%20to%20Wall%20Street.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompanies%20have%20framed%20this%20debate%20around%20profit%20maximization.%20And%20so%20as%20a%20result%2C%20people%20see%20it%20as%20zero-sum%2C%26quot%3B%20Ravi%20Dhar%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20and%20marketing%20and%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Customer%20Insights%20at%20the%20Yale%20School%20of%20Management.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20don't%20like%20the%20fluctuations%20because%20you%20always%20feel%20like%20somehow%20it's%20exploiting%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConstant%20prices%20aren't%20guaranteed%20and%20never%20have%20been.%20Discounts%20and%20promotions%20are%20well-trodden%20retail%20tactics%2C%20and%20the%20invisible%20hand%20of%20the%20market%20moves%20on%20the%20principles%20of%20supply%20and%20demand.%20Every%20business%20wants%20to%20charge%20a%20higher%20price%20to%20customers%20who%20can%20and%20will%20pay%20more%20and%20a%20lower%20price%20to%20those%20who%20can't%20and%20won't%2C%20said%20Z.%20John%20Zhang%2C%20a%20marketing%20professor%20at%20Wharton%20who%20focuses%20on%20pricing.%20We%20can't%20blame%20consumers%20for%20feeling%20like%20it%20adds%20uncertainty%20to%20an%20already%20tumultuous%20world%2C%20he%20said%2C%20but%20this%20is%20sort%20of%20the%20way%20things%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20big%20picture%2C%20there%20is%20actually%20no%20presumption%20for%20a%20constant%20price%20for%20a%20long%20time%20for%20a%20particular%20product%2C%20and%20the%20reason%20is%20that's%20not%20what%20prices%20are%20supposed%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20price%20is%20supposed%20to%20do%20is%20to%20mediate%20between%20demand%20and%20supply%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20product%20is%20really%20delivered%20into%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20right%20people%2C%20the%20right%20customers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20sounds%20fine%20and%20good%2C%20except%20we%20do%20not%20live%20in%20a%20world%20where%20markets%20are%20perfectly%20efficient%2C%20and%20nobody%20wants%20to%20be%20constantly%20watching%20for%20changing%20prices%20throughout%20their%20day.%20Many%20industries%20are%20uncompetitive%2C%20meaning%20consumers%20aren't%20even%20getting%20a%20fair%20shake.%20Plenty%20of%20companies%20can%20move%20their%20prices%2C%20whether%20by%20using%20dynamic%20prices%20or%20downright%20raising%20prices%2C%20because%20they're%20the%20only%20game%20in%20town.%20That's%20true%20for%20airlines%20and%20car-rental%20companies%20and%20wireless%20providers.%20It's%20why%20if%20you%20call%20your%20internet%20company%20to%20threaten%20to%20change%20services%20unless%20your%20bill%20stops%20creeping%20up%2C%20the%20answer%20you'll%20probably%20get%20is%20%26quot%3BLOL%20good%20luck%20with%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20airlines%2C%20if%20you%20asked%20people%2030%20years%20ago%20if%20they%20wanted%20to%20pay%20different%20prices%2C%20they'd%20be%20like%2C%20'No%20way%2C%20it's%20not%20fair%2C'%26quot%3B%20Webb%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20airline%20also%20knows%20that%2C%20hey%2C%20there's%20limited%20providers%20here%2C%20so%20competition%20does%20matter%2C%20and%20if%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20pay%2C%20well%2C%20that's%20fine.%20We're%20still%20at%20this%20price.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETechnology%20is%20a%20modern-day%20X-factor%20as%20well.%20Amazon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F02%2F26%2Ftechnology%2Famazon-price-swings-shopping.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echanges%20the%20prices%20of%20various%20items%3C%2Fa%3E%20throughout%20the%20day.%20Both%20Uber%20and%20DoorDash%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Fmoney%2F24105250%2Ffast-food-restaurants-dynamic-pricing-algorithm-wendys%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccused%20of%20displaying%20higher%20prices%20for%20certain%20customers%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20low%20phone%20batteries%20or%20those%20with%20iPhones%2C%20though%20both%20companies%20have%20denied%20this.%20Today's%20Blue%20Light%20Special%20is%20no%20longer%20in%20a%20store%20aisle%20on%20a%20Wednesday%20at%20noon%3B%20it's%20on%20a%20website%20that%20knows%20exactly%20who%20you%20are%20and%20is%20intimately%20familiar%20with%20your%20spending%20habits.%20Companies%20can%20use%20your%20data%20to%20identify%20an%20exact%20price%20%3Cem%3Efor%20you%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20may%20work%20in%20your%20favor%20but%20may%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20of%20this%20optimization%2C%20it%20reduces%20trust%20in%20the%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20Dhar%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20trust%20them%20to%20do%20things%20that%20are%20good%20for%20me.%20They're%20going%20to%20do%20things%20that%20are%20good%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20companies%20were%20more%20transparent%20about%20what%20they%20were%20doing%20and%20how%2C%20it%20might%20ease%20some%20discomfort.%20But%20many%20aren't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20no%20easy%20solutions%20here.%20Most%20economists%20agree%20that%20government-mandated%20price%20fixing%20is%20a%20bad%20idea.%20Achieving%20a%20more%20competitive%20economy%20is%20a%20long-term%20project%20that%20won't%20happen%20overnight.%20Inflation%20is%20getting%20better%2C%20but%20the%20threat%20of%20it%20getting%20worse%20again%20still%20looms.%20The%20answer%20to%20getting%20accustomed%20to%20high%20prices%20is%20basically%20to%20forget%20what%20those%20numbers%20were%20in%202019.%20We%20didn't%20even%20get%20into%20hidden%20fees%2C%20another%20layer%20in%20the%20what-does-anything-even-cost-and-why%20maze.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can't%20fault%20anyone%20for%20feeling%20tired%20of%20it%20all.%20After%20so%20much%20economic%20uncertainty%2C%20and%20with%20more%20uncertainty%20ahead%2C%20we're%20all%20in%20our%20feelings%20about%20prices.%20A%20prix%20fixe%20menu%20sounds%20pretty%20good%20right%20now%2C%20just%20to%2C%20for%20a%20moment%2C%20know%20what%20we're%20getting%20into%20cost-wise%20and%20enjoy%20a%20meal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-dynamic-pricing-surge-cost-fatigue-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720605243000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668d8ca3b2528216eeb4e284%3Ffor