n-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-3-1720083510-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-3-1720083510-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-355534%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ETiwari%20was%20joined%20by%20villagers%20who%20saw%20their%20efforts%20as%20a%20service%20to%20God%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Tiwari%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20plan%20to%20change%20the%20landscape%20of%20Bundelkhand%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConceiving%20change%20in%20a%20region%20that%20had%20almost%20succumbed%20to%20acute%20drought%20was%20a%20challenge%2C%20Tiwari%20points%20out.%20Moreover%2C%20because%20the%20villagers%20had%20lost%20hope.%20The%20young%20graduate%E2%80%99s%20plan%20was%20simple.%20He%20would%20return%20home%20every%20weekend%20from%20Allahabad%20where%20he%20was%20studying%2C%20and%20mobilise%20the%20people%20of%20his%20village%20to%20desilt%20the%20ponds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20observed%20that%20the%20ponds%20had%20a%20great%20capacity%2C%20but%20because%20they%20were%20choked%20with%20silt%2C%20their%20water%20accumulation%20capacity%20had%20gone%20down.%20So%2C%20even%20during%20the%20monsoons%2C%20the%20entire%20pond%20could%20not%20be%20filled.%20Come%20January%20every%20year%2C%20we%20faced%20water%20shortage%20again%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElaborating%20on%20the%20story%20of%20the%20first%20pond%20of%20focus%20%E2%80%98Bajrang%20Sagar%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20pond%20with%20an%2011%20%3Cem%3Ebigha%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20traditional%20unit%20to%20measure%20the%20area%20of%20a%20plot%20of%20land%3B%201%20%3Cem%3Ebigha%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3D%20%E2%85%93%20to%201%20acre)%20capacity%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20one%20of%20the%20major%20water%20bodies%20in%20the%20village%20and%20situated%20right%20near%20Hanuman%20Mandir.%20When%20I%20would%20call%20people%20to%20desilt%20the%20pond%20initially%2C%20they%20weren%E2%80%99t%20ready.%20So%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20keep%20prayers%20at%20the%20%3Cem%3Emandir%20%3C%2Fem%3E(temple)%20and%20people%20started%20coming%20in%20hordes.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-4-1720083584.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Desilting%20the%20Bajrang%20Sagar%20pond%20took%20a%20total%20of%20eight%20weeks%20with%20the%20villagers%20putting%20in%2024%20hours%20of%20work%20each%20week%2C%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-4-1720083584.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-4-1720083584-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-4-1720083584-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-4-1720083584-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-4-1720083584-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-355537%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EDesilting%20the%20Bajrang%20Sagar%20pond%20took%20a%20total%20of%20eight%20weeks%20with%20the%20villagers%20putting%20in%2024%20hours%20of%20work%20each%20week%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Tiwari%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETiwari%20and%20a%20few%20chosen%20friends%20began%20explaining%20the%20importance%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F281458%2Fenvironment-activist-revives-water-bodies-lakes-coimbatore-water-warrior-award%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edesilting%20the%20pond%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20devotees%20who%20had%20gathered.%20That%20day%2C%20before%20%3Cem%3Eprasada%3C%2Fem%3E%20(food%20and%20water%20offered%20to%20devotees)%20was%20distributed%2C%20the%20crowd%20pulled%20up%20their%20sleeves%20and%20began%20digging%20the%20silt%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPeople%20began%20seeing%20the%20job%20as%20manual%20labour%20that%20they%20were%20offering%20to%20God%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tiwari%20explains.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20time%2C%20more%20and%20more%20people%20began%20coming%20for%20this%20weekly%20effort.%20It%20took%20eight%20weeks%2C%20with%20us%20digging%20for%2024%20hours%20every%20Monday%2C%20for%20the%20pond%20to%20be%20completely%20cleared.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20points%20out%20that%20there%20was%20no%20compulsion%20or%20compensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20monsoon%20of%202015%20was%20phenomenal%20for%20the%20village%20of%20Adhawan%20which%20stood%20stunned%20as%20the%20pond%20filled%20up%20to%20its%2011%20%3Cem%3Ebigha%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecapacity.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20water%20quantity%20was%20so%20much%20that%20farmers%20could%20even%20use%20it%20for%20their%20irrigation%20needs%2C%20aside%20from%20people%20using%20the%20water%20for%20their%20home%20and%20personal%20needs%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tiwari%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-5-1720083725.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20pond%20that%20Tiwari%20and%20the%20villagers%20of%20Adhawan%20dug%20spanned%2011%20bighas%2C%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-5-1720083725.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-5-1720083725-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-5-1720083725-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-5-1720083725-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fpond-revival-in-villages-5-1720083725-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-355541%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20pond%20that%20Tiwari%20and%20the%20villagers%20of%20Adhawan%20dug%20spanned%2011%20bighas%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Tiwari%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20in%20the%20case%20of%20any%20village%2C%20Adhawan%20was%20witnessing%20migration.%20People%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20see%20a%20reason%20to%20live%20in%20a%20drought-prone%20region%20anymore%2C%20Tiwari%20explains.%20%E2%80%9CFour%20to%20five%20families%20had%20moved%20from%20the%20village%20and%20found%20jobs%20as%20security%20guards%20and%20drivers%20in%20Delhi%20and%20Pune.%20But%20when%20they%20heard%20about%20the%20success%20of%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F199310%2Fmumbai-man-revives-traditional-ponds-vasai-virar-water-hero-inspiring-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20pond%20revival%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20started%20making%20plans%20to%20return%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDismantling%20social%20constructs%20was%20exciting%20for%20Tiwari%20and%20his%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20crux%20on%20which%20their%20water%20project%20had%20been%20founded%20was%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EGaav%20ka%20paani%20gaav%20mein%2C%20khet%20ka%20paani%20khet%20mein%20%3C%2Fem%3E(The%20water%20of%20the%20village%20should%20remain%20in%20the%20village%2C%20and%20the%20water%20of%20the%20fields%20should%20be%20restricted%20to%20the%20fields.)%20To%20ensure%20this%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20started%20desilting%20many%20ponds%20around%20Bundelkhand%20across%20the%20villages%20of%20Marka%2C%20Pindaran%2C%20Gahbra%2C%20Jhalokhar%2C%20Mohnipur%20among%20others.%20We%20also%20started%20building%20troughs%20of%20two%20feet%20height%20around%20every%20field%20so%20that%20the%20rainwater%20could%20collect%20in%20this%20and%20be%20used%20for%20farming%20purposes%20even%20after%20the%20monsoons.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Foa--noZyZ1g%3Fsi%3DPCal_G3LmdeNRJu6%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETiwari%20and%20his%20team%20also%20organised%3Cem%3E%20paani%20chaupals%3C%2Fem%3E%20(water%20awareness%20sessions)%20where%20they%20challenged%20the%20villagers%20to%20question%20their%20water%20usage%2C%20and%20water-saving%20techniques.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20conducted%20over%20300%20of%20these%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tiwari%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20also%20started%20making%20water%20friends%20who%20we%20call%20%E2%80%98jal%20mitras%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%20Sharing%20more%20about%20this%20concept%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CTheir%20work%20is%20to%20focus%20on%20their%20respective%20villages%2C%20research%20water%20bodies%20and%20their%20capacities%2C%20work%20with%20tank%20management%20committees%20to%20see%20which%20ponds%20can%20be%20revived%20and%20create%20awareness%20about%20water%20conservation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Tiwari%20has%20a%20network%20of%205%2C000%20water%20friends%20across%20Bundelkhand.%20%E2%80%9CI%20will%20not%20be%20around%20forever.%20I%20wanted%20to%20ensure%20that%20my%20work%20continues%20even%20if%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20smiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3